title: turkey dressing casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top according to box.
Pour into a casserole dish. Place turkey over stuffing.
Then spoon soup over turkey.
Spread evenly.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 300° or 15 minutes in microwave.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers, salt and onions in a large container.
Cover with ice.
Let sit 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Bring to just below boiling.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: french fried zucchini
directions: Clean and slice zucchini (do not peel).
Put zucchini, pepper and salt into enough water to cover.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain. Beat eggs with 1 tablespoon water.
Dip zucchini in flour, then in egg, then again in flour.
Deep fry or panfry in Crisco.
Make sure oil is hot.

title: pinto beans -n- ham
directions: Soak beans overnight with plenty of water; add to beans, onion and trimmed ham (bite size).
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Boil slowly for 2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently.
An 8-quart pot is best.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in liberal amount of butter.
Add cooked beef; mix well.
Add flour and seasonings to your taste. Lastly, add enough water to make gravy.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and then place in crock-pot. Add all remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Heat on high for 3 hours or on low most of the day.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Place casserole in pan of water to bake! Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry fruit medley
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Add enough water to fill the blender 3/4 full.
Blend for 1 to 2 minutes or until blended. Serve chilled.

title: breakfast bran muffins
directions: *Or sufficient to make a thick dough.

title: hot fruit dessert
directions: *Canned, drained pineapple, pears or peaches, cut in chunks, dried apricots and prunes, cut in chunks, fresh apples, cored and sliced or maraschino cherries (if desired).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop stems with celery, onion and green pepper.
Saute in butter.
Add this to cream cheese, bread crumbs and lemon juice.
Mix well and stuff mushroom caps.
Place mushrooms, stuffed side up, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked steak
directions: Pound steak, cut in average pieces.
Flour on both sides.
Fry in Crisco.
Brown on both sides.
Place meat in baking dish.
Make gravy using about 1/2 cup flour, salt and enough water to thicken. Pour over meat in baking dish.
Cover with foil, leaving a small place open.
Bake for 1 hour in 400° oven.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown meat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Combine with next four ingredients.
Using large casserole or baking dish layer noodles, meat and onion-cheese mixture. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pecan bread
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten egg; beat until light.
Add melted butter; blend.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir just enough to blend.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all the cheese at room temperature.
Mix with an electric mixer to form ball.
Roll ball of cheese in finely chopped pecans.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: First line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Take the 40 crackers and lay out on cookie sheet.
In saucepan, put the margarine and the brown sugar and bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Then just pour over the crackers.
Place in a 400° oven for 5 minutes and when it comes out of the oven, sprinkle the morsels on top.
As they melt spread over the crackers.
Let set up and break into pieces.

title: easy bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Split buns lengthwise into quarters. Combine garlic salt, basil and parsley with margarine.
Spread cut surfaces with mixture; place on cookie sheet.
Bake until crisp and lightly browned, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Store in tightly covered container.
Serve with soup or as an appetizer.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Heat syrup and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: tomato rice
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water for 14 minutes.
Drain. While rice is cooking, stew tomatoes gently for about 10 minutes. Add a little water if necessary.
Press through a sieve.
Return to low heat and add seasoning.
Mix well.
Stir into the hot rice and sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken curry
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot with water and bouillon.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until tender.
Remove from broth and cool.
Remove chicken from bones and dice.
Peel, core and dice apple.
Saute in butter with onion, celery and curry powder until limp and glazed.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Add diced chicken and enough broth to moisten.
Cook on low until hot.
Serve over rice.
Pass condiments.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Blend soda and buttermilk, stir well. Pour sugar in large boiler; add milk mixture, syrup and margarine.
Bring to boil; cook to 240° on thermometer or medium soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in buttered dish or drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and remove seeds from peppers and place in baking dish.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Drain.
Stir in salt, rice, garlic salt and 1 cup tomato sauce. Lightly stuff peppers.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over stuffed peppers.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Saute garlic in Dutch oven or similar sized pan on med. heat until flavor starts to release.
Add cubed chicken breast and cook until done, but be careful not to brown.
You may notice some liquid forming while you cook the chicken.
That's okay because it just adds to the flavor.
When chicken is done, add the beans and reduce heat to med-low.
When beans have heated, add the salsa. Remember that usually heating intensifies how spicy hot it is.
I usually use either mild or med. salsa.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix marinade ingredients and pour over flank steak.
Marinate overnight or at least 4 hours, in refrigerator, turning several times.
Grill.
Best if served rare to medium-rare.
Slice thinly across the grain.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Cut English muffins in half.
Mix tomato sauce with herbs in a small bowl.
Spread tomato mixture on muffins.
Arrange thinly sliced onion, pepper, olives and cheese on top.
Place muffin halves on a cookie sheet and put under the broiler about 4 inches from heat.
Broil until cheese bubbles, leaving oven door open. Serve hot.
Optional topping:
vegetarian sausage.

title: jelly roll
directions: Add slightly beaten egg yolks to 1/2 cup boiling water.
Beat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Fold sugar into egg mixture; add flavoring. Pour into 14 x 18-inch pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out on towel; spread with jelly and roll up.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix buttermilk, oil and eggs together.
Then add all other ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chunky granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place oats, sunflower seeds or nuts, coconut, wheat germ and bran in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all but raisins; bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
After baking, add raisins.
Excellent sprinkled on ice cream or frozen yogurt.
It's not just for breakfast at our house!
A good source of fiber.
Makes one gallon.

title: breakfast casserole (2)
directions: Roll crescent rolls into 9 X 13 greased pan.
Mix eggs with milk. Combine ingredients together and pour into pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: mini cheese balls(makes approximately 35 balls.)
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into individual balls.
Roll in chipped beef.

title: pink arctic frozen salad
directions: Soften cheese and blend with mayonnaise and sugar.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add more crushed pineapple and/or Cool Whip if you want to make a larger salad.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan and freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Set out 15 minutes before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Pack crackers and butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add ice cream.
Beat just until smooth.
Pour onto cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: holly cookies
directions: Put oleo or butter and marshmallows in a good size pan.
Melt on medium-low heat, then add food coloring.
Stir, then add corn flakes.
Stir until flakes are coated.
Drop onto wax paper.
Add 3 red candies immediately.
Refrigerate until hard.
Need my wife to help.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Put some of the tomatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish. Layer with lasagne.
Layer with cottage cheese that has been mixed with eggs.
Layer with each cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients have been used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 375° for 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice cabbage and boil in a lot of salted water until softened; drain.
Cut potatoes into small pieces; add diced onion. Mix in cabbage; add oil, cider vinegar, salt and pepper to taste and toss.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese with water until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into chocolate graham cracker crust.
Pour small amount of chocolate syrup on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Put in freezer for 1 1/2 or 2 hours. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: roast beef
directions: Wash meat and dry thoroughly using paper towels.
Pierce the meat and make a few gashes with a knife.
Marinate with all the ingredients and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients, excluding mushrooms. Blanch stemmed mushrooms in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain and add to marinade.
Refrigerate in tightly sealed container for 24 to 48 hours.
Pour off marinade and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Then cream shortening, sugar and yolks.
Add chocolate mixture to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 prepared cake pans or loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tri-color pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Prepare all other ingredients and toss in a large bowl.
Add salad dressing and toss well.
When pasta is cooked, drain and rinse in cold water until completely cool.
Add to salad and toss again.
Serve chilled.
Best when made the day before. Parmesan cheese is optional and can be added when served.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown ground beef and hot sausage.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; beat (no milk or butter).
Add cream cheese with chives, egg and then sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 1-quart casserole (greased) at 373° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello with water; chill until partially set.
Grind up other ingredients and add to partially set jello.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking power, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, eggs and water; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats, Nestle butterscotch morsels and orange extract.
Drop by slightly rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix corn, baby peas, green beans, onions, celery, green pepper and pimento together.
Combine sugar, white vinegar, pepper, oil and salt.
Mix well and add to vegetables.
Mix again and marinate overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt oleo in 10-inch glass pie plate or microwave Bundt pan on High.
Coat biscuits with oleo.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Dip biscuits in sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits in a ring in pan.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 minutes on High power.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream cheese should be at room temperature.
With a mixer, whip cream cheese and add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix until smooth, mix in lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
This can be topped with your favorite pie filling.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add chopped onion, chopped green pepper, salt and garlic salt.
Cook spaghetti.
Add mushrooms or mushroom soup and tomato soup to hamburger meat mixture.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Put in casserole and put layer of Velveeta, Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 375° to 400 ° until cheese melts.

title: sweet and sour mustard sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Blend in eggs, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce to form a smooth paste.
Over low heat, gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Serve with cheese balls, crackers, summer sausage and mustard.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll bread until flat.
Put 1/2 pound of sausage and 1/2 pound of ground beef in skillet.
Drain and spread over rolled out pastry.
Add cheese of your choice and any seasonings you like. Roll up.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Chill in refrigerator until thickened enough to beat.
Blend thickened jello and chilled evaporated milk in blender.
Cream together in small bowl the cream cheese (softened) and sugar.
Add cream cheese mixture to jello mixture.
Add vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Blend quickly just to mix together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill several hours or overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer hamburger, then green beans, then soup.
Last, layer mashed potatoes.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatine with cold water.
Add hot water and lemon juice. Let cool and add pineapple and sugar.
Mix in Dream Whip.
Crumble 1 angel food cake and line pan with cake pieces.
Pour mixture over cake.
Let set overnight.
Ice with 1 package Dream Whip and coconut.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.

title: rachael's favorite banana bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk/vinegar mixture.
Add mashed bananas.
Spray two loaf pans with nonstick spray.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans when completely cool.

title: chili "no bean" dip
directions: Layer cream cheese.
Spread chili.
Spread chili peppers, then spread Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes. Microwave for about 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese, then cover with cheese.

title: roast pork and potatoes
directions: Take pork out of refrigerator an hour in advance.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Rub meat with garlic and salt.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in shallow open pan.
Roast pork 1 hour at 425°. Reduce heat to 400°.
Remove pork from pan and pour off all fat.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. Stir in milk until smooth; cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Remove from the heat. Gradually stir about 1 cup of hot mixture into beaten eggs. Return all to saucepan. Bring to a gentle boil. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Remove from the heat. Stir in 1 cup coconut, butter and vanilla. Pour into pie crust; sprinkle with remaining coconut. Chill for several hours before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Mix together the cake mix, egg and Cool Whip; set aside.
Sift powdered sugar.
Drop cookie mix by spoonful into powdered sugar; cover entirely.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Low in fat.

title: strawberry sugar-free jello cake
directions: Combine strawberries with jello mixture.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in a glass casserole dish.
Pour jello/strawberry liquid over cake until jello saturates cake. Chill until firm.
Top with lite Cool Whip and dot with whole strawberries.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups, gummy worms and frogs, candy flowers, etc.

title: caramel pop corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally
and
boil 5 minutes.	Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda (will foam, so use rather large pot).
Stir over bowls
of
popped
corn.
Place
in
large flat pans or cookie sheets.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon. Pour into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Place bacon on top; bake uncovered for about 40 minutes at 350°. Broil a few minutes to make bacon crisp. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Place half the mushrooms, a layer of cheese, half the stuffing and half the seasoning mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat these layers one more time.

title: peanut butter fudge (6 minutes)
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 6 minutes and add fluff, vanilla, peanut butter and salt.
Set in pan to harden.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter together. (Crunchy peanut butter may be used if you don't have the peanuts and it is as good.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and peanuts.
Add chow mein noodles last, stirring very carefully. Let set.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 13 pan.
Top with 2 cups hand crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: swiss chicken and ham roll-ups
directions: In mixing bowl, combine chicken, 1/3 can soup and onion.
Spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture on each ham slice and roll up.
Secure with toothpick, if necessary.
Spread rice in shallow 1 1/2-quart microwave dish.
Place roll-ups on top of rice.
Mix remaining soup with sour cream and milk.
Pour over ham rolls.
Cook on High 12 to 14 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: tiger striped fudge
directions: Melt white chocolate.
Stir in peanut butter.
Spread into waxed paper lined pan (jelly roll).
Melt chocolate chips in microwave according to package directions.
Stir chocolate chips into pan immediately after white chocolate.
Take a butter knife and turn back and forth through chocolates to make swirls. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sit out at room temperature before cutting fudge.

title: potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat and stir in catsup, mustard, paprika and salt until well mixed.
Cut each potato into 4 wedges.
Slash each wedge crosswise at 1/4-inch intervals, but do not cut through skin.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bowl. Stir to mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until combined.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour evenly over batter in pan.
Sprinkle over top a mixture of the 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve warm. A wonderful coffee cake.

title: company pot roast
directions: Rub roast with flour on both sides and brown well on all sides. Place in roaster.
Sprinkle with next 5 ingredients.
Pat bread crumbs on roast.
Tie in a cloth bag, celery, cloves, bay leaf and parsley.
Place bag on roast.
Arrange olives, carrots and mushrooms around roast.
Pour in wine.
Roast for 5 hours in 250° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending into mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into graham cracker shell; sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: brown oatmeal rolls
directions: Pour water over rolled oats; cool.
Add salad oil softened in lukewarm water, brown sugar and salt.
Beat in flour to make soft dough.
Knead; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut any shape desired.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put torn pieces of angel food cake into a large punch bowl. Pour crushed pineapple with juice over the pieces of cake.
Add strawberries the same way.
Put coconut, nuts next, then make pudding mix as directed on package.
Add bananas to this pudding. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: camper's casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti without salt.
Fry dried beef, onion and green pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, melted butter and sugar.
Stir in yogurt.
Add dry ingredients just until blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into muffin tins and bake 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans and preheat oven to 325°. Cream the eggs, sugar and oil. Add vanilla and all dry ingredients.
Beat well. Fold in zucchini and add raisins and pineapple.
Pour into pans and bake for 1 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place 1/2 taco shells in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
I skillet brown beef until crumbly; drain.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in onion and tomato sauce.
Spoon over taco shells.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese, rest of taco shells and remaining cheese.
Top with tomato wedges and olives.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spice cake speedy
directions: Pour into micro Bundt pan and microwave on High for 13 minutes. Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Scald milk and add cool water.
When lukewarm, add yeast, salt, eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well.
Add 4 more cups and stir.
Knead in about 1/2 cup more flour.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise to double.
Divide dough.
Roll in rectangles.
Butter and fold each in half.
Cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch strips.
Pull and twist and wind into a solid circle.
Let rise again.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend until well mixed.
Chill and serve with crackers, Melba Toast and fresh vegetables.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, sugar and soda.
Make hole in mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Cook in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spiced beets
directions: Cover
the
beets
with water and add onions; cover and boil for
hour
or
until
beets are tender.
Drain and add sugar, vinegar, cloves, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Mash beets and reheat over a low fire for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, nuts, oleo, salt and soda to a crumb state.
Put 3/4 crumb mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook remaining ingredients until thick and spread on top of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins and caraway seed. Add beaten egg, buttermilk and melted shortening.
Mix thoroughly. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead lightly for 1 minute. Shape in round loaf and place on greased pan.
Mark in quarters and dot each section with butter.
Allow to stand 10 to 15 minutes before baking in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a ball and chill.
Grease pizza pan and press pastry into pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese and sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage and mushrooms; drain.
Spoon into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over sausage mixture; cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Beat Cool Whip.
Add dry jello.
Fold in sour cream.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts.
Chill for 30 minutes or longer.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together in another bowl.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Will keep days in the refrigerator.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water for 10 minutes and drain well. Cook soups and cheese until melted.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water until completely dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and freeze in large molds.
At serving time, remove from freezer and place in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture and mix.
Serves 50.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix flour, sesame seed, salt, pepper and paprika.
In another pan put melted butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip chicken in butter mixture, then flour mixture.
Lay chicken in flat, slightly greased pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° oven until tender and golden brown.
If chicken does not brown well, put under broiler for approximately 5 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: In thick-bottomed pan, fry cut-up bacon and pour off grease. Add clams, potatoes and onion.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Add half and half and cook until thick over medium to medium-high heat.
Stir frequently.
Season to taste with butter, salt and pepper.

title: easy "d" jelly cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients
well and roll into 3/4-inch balls. Push thumb into each ball and fill with desired jam.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Put in rice and corn.
Salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Add onion, green pepper and and ground beef.
Salt and pepper again.

title: mom's spicy molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add molasses and dry ingredients; blend well.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Nice, soft and chewy.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Sift flour, soda, and salt together.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until blended.
Add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Chill.
Shape into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 - 11 minutes.
Press a kiss on each cookie while they're still hot.
Remove cookies from cookie sheet and cool on rack.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Coat chicken in cornstarch.
Mix sherry, ginger root and 2 ounces soy sauce.
Marinate chicken for 1 hour in refrigerator. Pat dry.
Deep fry in oil until golden.
Drain and let cool.
Cut into strips.
Toss chicken, onion, cilantro, almonds, sesame seed, etc.
(all other items).

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir with a fork until well mixed. Fry with 1 teaspoon of the mixture in hot oil until golden brown for about 3 minutes.
Drain on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in soup. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix until heated.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: reception salad
directions: Let jello set until real soft, not hard.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let set until firm.

title: cold macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Cut Spam into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: best crock-pot roast
directions: Mix.
Place some in crock-pot. Place roast in crock-pot.
Pour in rest of gravy.
Cook to taste.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable mushroom rice
directions: Cook rice, then add Veg-All, mushrooms and onions.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
In large frying pan, combine sesame seeds and oil; cook over medium/low heat stirring occasionally until seeds are golden (about 2 minutes).
Let cool and add soy sauce, sugar, ginger, pepper, garlic and HALF the green onions.
Add chicken, cover and chill 1-4 hours.
Arrange chicken with the marinade in a single layer in a 10X15 baking pan. Broil about 6 inches from the heat until golden (about 10 minutes).
Turn pieces over and continue broiling until chicken is no longer pink inside (about 5 minutes longer).
Serve over rice and garnish with remaining onions.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix in large bowl with a spoon the white and brown sugars, egg, then margarine.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Let cookies cool on cooling sheet.

title: savory liver dip
directions: Combine sour cream and dry onion mix.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add steak sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Add sour cream mixture and mix.
Add liver sausage and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers or snack rye bread.

title: fresh blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: birdseed snack
directions: *Add or subtract to taste.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Melt Andes chocolate in a saucepan.
Using a food processor or blender, chop pecans into very fine pieces.
Prepare pound cake and mix as directed.
Add Andes chocolate and pecans.
Bake according to directions.

title: swiss breakfast muesli
directions: Combine oats, yogurt, pineapple (drained) and almonds; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
To serve, layer in ice cream style parfait glasses.
Garnish with strawberries and almonds.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Marinate at least 2 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
By hand, shape into balls about 2 inches in diameter.
Bake in a large pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Bake last 15 minutes with sauce poured over balls, covering each one well.

title: pumpkin-snap mousse
directions: Spray loaf pan with cooking spray.
In saucepan, combine pudding and gelatin.
Gradually whisk in milk.
Bring to boil while whisking.
Remove from heat.
Whisk in pumpkin and vanilla.
Place pan in a bowl of ice water.
Whisk until cool.
Whisk in all but 3/4 cup topping.
Pour 1/2 mousse into loaf pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup ginger snaps.
Top with remaining mousse.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.
Unmold and garnish with remaining topping and ginger snaps.

title: poe's tennessee river salmon
directions: Cut in about 1-inch squares.
Pack into jars.
The fish listed will all do the same thing, with the same taste.

After fish is packed into jars, put salt and vinegar into each jar and seal. Put into canner and cook for 110 minutes at 5 pounds of pressure. No one will ever know this is not salmon unless you tell them. Make salmon or tuna patties.
Also good for casseroles.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix pineapple, marshmallows and walnuts.
Let set 24 hours. Add cherries, mandarin oranges and bananas.
Add Dream Whip.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Mix together shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs. Mix well, then add flour, salt and soda.
Finally, add oats.
Roll batter in two rolls, in wax paper, about 2 1/2-inches thick. Place on pan in freezer.
Slice about 1/3-inch thick and bake as needed.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes at 375°.

title: tomatoes lutice
directions: Place tomatoes (peeled if desired) in a shallow non-metallic pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over tomatoes and let stand (or refrigerate) for several hours.
Serve.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Spread broccoli in bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice.
Spread over broccoli. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: tokyo chicken or drumsticks
directions: In baking dish (12
x
8 x 2-inches), stir together soy sauce, sherry,
water,
sugar,
onion
and
garlic.
Marinate chicken several hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, turn and bake 30 minutes or until tender.
Baste with sauce and serve with rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad; mix well and refrigerate up to 6 to 8 hours.
Serve chilled.
Amounts given are approximate.
Let taste be your guide!

title: hamburger buns
directions: Soak yeast in 1/2 cup warm water (105° to 115°).
Combine milk, sugar and salt.
Beat in shortening-yeast mixture and 2 cups flour with mixer.
Add remaining flour and mix in.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes until smooth.
Cover and let raise until double, 30 to 40 minutes. Punch down.
Shape into rolls or hamburger buns.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen dinner size rolls or 1 1/2 dozen hamburger buns.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water. Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag and add to vinegar mixture. Simmer 15 minutes. Pack cucumbers into hot Ball jars leaving 1/4 inch head space. Put a head of dill in each jar. Heat brine to boiling. Pour boiling hot vinegar mixture over cucumbers, leaving a 1/4 inch head space. Cover with a canning lid and ring. Place in canner of water. Boil for 15 minutes. Let cool and then remove jars. Yields about 7 pints.

title: meatballs or meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Add to spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring often and gently.

title: grape jello salad with topping
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Pour mixture into 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Place in refrigerator and allow Jell-O to set.

title: sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Use basic sourdough as needed to form a soft dough. Turn out onto a floured board.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Roll up and cut.
Place in greased pan. Bake approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown. Frost with powdered sugar glaze while still warm.

title: spanish corn bread
directions: Mix corn, cream, oil, peppers and cheese.
Add dry ingredients and eggs.
Mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins and hard-boil eggs.
(Boiling the day before is not a bad idea because they all have to be well cooled.)
Mix everything together except the eggs.
When everything is mixed up, add the eggs and mix just enough to stir them in.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate and butter melt, stirring constantly. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Beat at high speed of an electric mixer until of spreading consistency.
Immediately spread on cake.
Yield: enough for one 3-layer cake.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Combine raw macaroni and all other ingredients in casserole dish.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Flavor will soak in. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nut patties
directions: Blend together well with a spoon.
Make into patties.
Can be fried or baked.

title: tuna on a string salad
directions: Drain tuna; mix first 5 ingredients.
Just before serving, add shoestring potatoes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets and cook them until tender.
Be sure not to overcook them.
Take skins off, leaving whole if small.
If large, cut in halves or quarters.
Put vinegar, sugar and salt in 1 gallon or larger container.
Add beets; cook until they simmer. Place white mustard seed in jars and can the hot beets.

title: quick carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil celery and
onion	in
chicken broth until tender. Add undiluted soup and	mushrooms.
Add chicken and 1 cup chow mein noodles and mix just until blended.
Pour into casserole. Top with 1/2 cup chow
mein	noodles.
Bake	at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (approximately).

title: pull apart cake
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and roll biscuits in it.
Place in a greased Bundt pan.
Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and pecans in a saucepan.
Boil.
Pour over biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; refrigerate until ready to fill.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, with electric beater, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla; beat until well blended. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or just until filling is set in center.
(Shake pie gently; center should be firm.)
Let cool on wire rack.
May be garnished with whipped cream.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine beef, Parmesan cheese, dry bread crumbs, milk and egg. Shape into 20 meatballs.
Brown well in shortening.
Drain excess fat. Sprinkle flour over meatballs.
Stir gently to cover meatballs.
Combine tomatoes, Heinz 57 sauce, sugar and salt. Pour over meatballs.
Simmer uncovered 25 minutes or until sauce is desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Serve meatballs and sauce over prepared noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (do not overcook so pieces stay firm and crisp). Drain.
Set aside.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Carefully fold in broccoli.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil all ingredients, except popcorn and baking soda, for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put dry popcorn in a large bowl. Add baking soda to boiling ingredients and continue stirring. Will start to "grow" quickly.
Pour over popcorn and gently stir. Butter hands and form into balls.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat. Drain fat and set aside. Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth. Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper. Turn into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cutlet fajitas
directions: Slice cutlets to 1/4-inch strips.
Slice peppers and onion. Saute all ingredients until onion is clear.
Wrap in tortillas.

title: philly cream spread
directions: Chop cherries and mix with pineapple.
Stir into the cream cheese.
Spread on crackers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light and well blended.
Add oil, continuing to beat.
Combine dry ingredients and blend into egg mixture.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into well greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Let cake stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Then turn on rack to cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup with mayonnaise.
Add chicken, celery and almonds. Put in casserole and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix with pastry blender the margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Cream the cream cheese and 10x sugar; fold in Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Mix instant pudding, milk and lemon juice and beat until thick.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into 2 x 1/4-inch strips and brown in shortening.
Drain.
Add liquid from can of tomato wedges, onion, garlic, gravy base, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Cover tightly and simmer on low for 50 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes from can and green peppers cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Cook, covered, about 6 to 8 minutes or until pepper is tender.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Beat eggs. Blend in sour cream, oil and corn.
Mix corn meal, salt and baking powder. Add to first mixture and stir just until blended.
Bake in greased muffin pans or 8-inch square baking pan 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bread bowl dip
directions: Mix ingredients together. Scoop out center of round loaf and scoop the mixture into the bowl. Use remaining bread to scoop out the dip.

title: low-fat applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar and Butter Buds.
Add baking soda to applesauce; add to Butter Buds mixture.
Blend well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add raisins and Grape-Nuts.
Chill dough for one hour.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate several hours.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pie filling and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inches).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make the Stove Top stuffing, using 2 cups of water for each box.
Pour 1/2 of the dressing in bottom of pan.
Add layer of chicken.
Mix both cans of soup with the milk.
Pour over chicken.
Beat the egg and mix with the rest of the dressing and spread on top of the soups.
Then pour 2 cups of chicken broth over the top (depending on how moist you want the casserole).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: miracle salmon loaf
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, egg, lemon juice, soup, onions, green pepper and salt.
Add bread crumbs and salmon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt 1/2 of chocolate chips and 1/2 of wax together.
Put thin layer of chocolate mix in bottom of petite baking cups.
Mix together powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Layer over chocolate.
Melt other half of chocolate and pour over peanut butter layers.

title: roast beef
directions: Place in large roaster pan.
Pour all the soups over the roast.
Put in oven (covered) for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Will make its own gravy.

title: dog biscuits(for pets)
directions: Mix all together. Flour board and roll dough with rolling pin. This dough will be nice and firm to roll out. Cut into squares like the size of purchased dog biscuits.
Lift square in hand and squeeze center like the shape of a bow tie.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 325° until baked or brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage and onions until done; drain.
Melt cheese and half stick margarine.
Pour on cabbage; stir well.
Put in dish and pour other half butter over cabbage.
Crumble crackers on top. Cook until good and hot and cheese is melted.

title: lush
directions: Follow directions on graham cracker crumb box for the crust. place on the bottom of 9x13 in cake pan.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Quarter and seed peppers.
Cut into very thin strips.
In medium size bowl, combine peppers and cabbage.
In jar with tight fitting lid, combine vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Shake vigorously to combine.
Pour over peppers and cabbage mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Toss before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to 260°.
Add
peanuts
and butter and boil until light brown in color.
Remove
from fire and add soda and vanilla which has been mixed
with 1 teaspoon water. Pour
on a well-greased cookie
sheet.
Spread
thin. Cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into frying skillet.
Brown and drain.
Spread bread crumbs into baking dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Beat egg, milk and seasonings; pour over sausage-cheese mixture.
Bake at 305° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sunday roast and gravy
directions: Place roast in a 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine soup with water, add vegetables and stir.
Pour on top of roast.
Cover tightly with foil.	Bake at 350° about 3 hours.
I put this in the oven on a Sunday morning and it's done when we return home. It smells wonderful upon entering your home.
Serves 6-8.

title: italian macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Meanwhile brown meat and onions in oil, then add the tomatoes, spices, and mushrooms and cook for 45 minutes.
Mix the meat sauce and macaroni and pour into a greased bowl; top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 min.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Prepare pudding mix by adding milk; add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer crackers and add pudding mix.
Begin and end with crackers (3 layers crackers and 2 layers of mix).
Top with chocolate mixture. Refrigerate.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by directions on can.
Add ginger ale and orange juice.
Spoon in sherbet one large spoon at a time until slightly melted.
Freeze strawberries in ice trays of water and float in punch for a pretty look.

title: crunchy vegetable bake
directions: Butter a 2-quart baking dish. Combine vegetables, onion and garlic. Pour soup over vegetables; sprinkle with croutons and paprika. Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: roxanne's potato pancakes
directions: Mix onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Peel and grate potatoes into onion mixture.
Mix well; pour oil to cover bottom of large skillet.
Heat skillet, drop potato mixture by large spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Serve hot with sour cream or applesauce. Makes about 15 or 16 potato pancakes.

title: light nut caramels
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, cream and butter in large (about 3-quart), heavy saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.

When mixture begins to caramelize, lower heat and cook, stirring constantly to 244° on a candy thermometer or until a teaspoonful of mixture dropped in cold water forms a ball that does not flatten when removed from water.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into one corner of a lightly buttered 8-inch square cake pan.
Allow mixture to flow and level of its own accord.
Let stand until cold.
Turn the block of candy onto a cutting board.
Mark off 3/4-inch squares; cut with a sharp knife. Wrap caramels individually in waxed paper.
Makes about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine soaked bread crumbs (with milk), ground beef, onion, salt, egg and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf in lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining barbecue sauce and the water.
Pour about 1/4 cup of mixture over meat loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° basting often with remaining sauce.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind Spam and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on 1/2 of hamburger buns.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup flour, mixed with salt, baking soda and fructose.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Put dough in greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool bread on its side.
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Makes 18 slices.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in meal and fry.

title: hard times dessert #2
directions: Sprinkle sugar on piece of white bread and sprinkle lightly with water.

title: guacamole dip #1
directions: Mix avocados with cream cheese and season to taste.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Brown the ground beef.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer.
Cook noodles.
In pan, place layer of sauce, then cottage cheese mix, Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses and 4 lasagna noodles.
Repeat.
Top layer should include sauce and cheeses. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine sugar, salt, syrup and egg whites in top of double boiler.
Stir and add water.
Place over boiling water for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add extract and beat vigorously with rotary beater or electric mixer on high speed until icing forms peaks.

title: hazeline's fruit dip
directions: With mixer, mix cream cheese till soft, add brown sugar and beat together till creamy.

title: south dakota cheesecake
directions: Make graham cracker crust for 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Cool evaporated milk and warm cream cheese.
Dissolve Jell-O in water. In blender, combine milk, cheese, Jell-O and lime juice.
Pour into pie and freeze.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, eggs, evaporated milk, sugar and spices. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour oleo and nuts over cake mix.
Bake in a 300° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, pork, onion and garlic in large saucepan until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off all fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and basil. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 1 hour or until the consistency of
spaghetti sauce. Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and oregano. Reserve 1/2 cup meat sauce for thin top layer.

title: butterscotch candies
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Slowly stir in noodles and peanuts.
Spoon onto waxed paper and refrigerate until set.

title: monkey rolls
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a Ziploc bag.
Roll biscuits into balls, then shake into sugar mixture.
Place sugar coated balls into a greased round baking pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar in a saucepan and melt completely. Pour over dough balls.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven and turn upside down on a plate while hot and fresh from the oven.

title: jello shots
directions: Pour package of Jello mix into bowl. Add 1 cup boiling water. Stir to dissolve. Stir in vodka. Pour mixture into mold or pan. Freeze until firm. Cut into individual servings or use individual disposable shot cups (available at party stores). Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: beef log
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften before mixing ingredients. Combine cream cheese, Accent, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Place chipped beef in food processor to chop.
Then combine chipped beef with mixed ingredients.
Reserve a small portion of chipped beef to roll log in.
The log should be covered in chipped beef.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together.
Pour into a bunt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop by scant spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat oil in wok and fry chicken until tender or white.
Season with salt.
Add green pepper, onions, and syrup drained from pineapple.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and water; stir this mixture into chicken.
Cook until thickened.
Stir pineapple chunks and chow mein vegetables.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Add snow peas or water chestnuts if desired.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add seasonings.
Mix corn, tomatoes and tomato sauce, corn meal, olives and milk in separate bowl.
Add meat and onion last.
Corn meal absorbs liquids so be sure mixture is quite juicy.
Place mixture in large casserole dish, placed in larger pan of water.
Bake in hot oven (425° to 450°) for about 1 hour.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole dish combine soup and sour cream. Stir in broccoli, ham and rice.
Mix well.
Add butter to bread crumbs; stir well and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: gram's fudge frosting
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and salt.
Add sugar and cream.
Mix and boil over low fire for 3 minutes.
Stir until you hear cracking sound.
Spread on cake.
Double recipe for use on angel food or full size.

title: oysters casino
directions: Fry bacon until partially cooked.
Add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Add lemon juice and seasonings.
Arrange oysters in well-greased shallow baking pan.
Spread bacon mixture over oysters.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Serve as an appetizer or over toast points.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add cornmeal and flour and mix well. Add eggs, vanilla, pineapple and coconut.
Pour in pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix in lunch bowl; blend on medium-high speed until thick. Sprinkle top with cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in a small amount of water. Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onions in a little bacon drippings.
Mix all together, put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In large pot, boil split chicken breast, diced celery and diced carrots for 30 minutes (season with black pepper).
Turn down burner to low/medium.
Remove chicken from pot and shred.
Return chicken to pot.
Add all cans of soup.
Stir occasionally.
Once heated, serve with crackers.

title: white cake supreme
directions: Cream shortening, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into two greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: turkey paprika
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in skillet.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Blend in flour and salt.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens. Reduce heat and add paprika.
Add mushrooms and turkey.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Add poppy seed and 2 tablespoons butter to drained, cooked noodles.
Toss together lightly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam squash, carrots and onion until tender.
Drain in colander, mashing out water with spoon.
Remove all excess water.
Meanwhile, melt 1/4 cup margarine in a skillet over medium heat.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Then gradually add milk; stir 1 more minute.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Remove from heat; add sour cream and pimientos to squash mixture.
Fold into skillet mixture.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add corn and tomato soup.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: old-fashioned crumb cake
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
To the rest of the crumbs, add 3/4 cup sour milk or buttermilk, vanilla and 2 teaspoons soda dissolved in 1 teaspoons water.
Pour into greased loaf cake pan and bake.
Sprinkle the crumbs on top and bake.

title: face paints
directions: In muffin tins, add all ingredients (a different color in each tin).
Stir and you're set!
Now paint the funniest face you can.

title: butter flavored snack crackers
directions: Pour oil and ranch dressing in a large bowl and stir well. Add crackers, stir to coat.
Put lid on bowl and flip container throughout the day to coat crackers.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Grease (with canola oil) and flour 2 standard loaf pans.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add cranberry sauce and mix thoroughly. Mix in remaining ingredients and pour into the prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans.

title: chocolate fudge dessert
directions: Place chips, margarine and nuts in a large bowl, then boil sugar, marshmallows and evaporated milk for 6 minutes; don't overcook.
Pour over bowl items and beat.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan, lined with waxed paper, and cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter; bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until melted. Add oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Take off of bone and cut into small pieces.
Mix chicken broth, chicken soup, peas, carrots and potatoes with chicken and pour into a baking dish (8 x 13-inch).

title: granny's cornmeal pie
directions: Blend sugars and butter. Add egg yolks and vanilla. Cream together.
Add corn meal, nuts and coconut. Blend together. Beat egg whites and add in. Blend and pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. It's g-o-o-d.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, melted butter, flour and milk. Mix well and add coconut.
Pour into 2 ungreased 9-inch pie plates.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
It makes its own crust!

title: buttery sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Stir in flour.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli.
Shake well.
Pour over broccoli and set for 24 hours.
Drain and eat.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; make balls and brown in 350° oven. Put into slow cooker and add chili sauce, grape jelly and water. Cook on high for 1 hour and then on low for at least 2 hours.
Can add 1 cup sour cream but not necessary.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package. Rinse and drain well. Add all of the ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate until served.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Line 9-inch pie plate with bottom crust; add filling and dot with butter. To prepare a lattice top, roll out remaining crust and cut into 1/2-inch strips. On top of pie, make an "x" with 2 strips in the center of pie. Continue weaving strips allowing space between each strip. Trim edges and crimp top and bottom crust together. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl; cut in peanut butter with pastry blender or fork until mixture is crumbly.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of butter into muffin pans; spoon 1 teaspoon jelly into center of batter and top with additional butter, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sugar-free jelly may be substituted.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Squeeze 2 teaspoons of juice from lemon and set aside.
Cook chicken in hot oil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Set aside.
In skillet, add soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes (make sure chicken is not pink), stirring often.

title: cheesy tuna twists
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, melt butter and cooked vegetables and garlic for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Add soup to skillet, stirring until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk. Add cheese, dash of pepper and nutmeg; heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tuna and cooked macaroni.
Heat through.
Garnish with pimento.
Makes 6 cups.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir just until moistened. Pour into a greased 1-1/2 quart baking pan. Sprinkle with blackberries. Pour juice over all. Bake at 350° for 45 - 50 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm; top with ice cream or whipped cream if desired.

title: chocolate chip cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients but chocolate chips and syrup.
Put half of batter in bowl and add chocolate chips and chocolate syrup. Put half of the yellow mixture in baking pan.
Then add half of chocolate mixture.
Put the rest of the yellow in pan and finish with the rest of the chocolate mixture.
Swirl a little with a knife.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Don't overbake!

title: kathy's turkey and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions on package.
Cook broccoli in seasoning package from stuffing, in 1 3/4 cups water. Mix in large bowl and put half in casserole.
Add onion rings. Cover with remaining dressing, broccoli mixture.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and cook 8 more minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Blend jello to the Cool Whip, then blend in the fruit cocktail and then the cottage cheese and top with spoonfuls of Cool Whip and cherries.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well, then add 6 well beaten eggs. Pour into 2 frozen pie crusts.
Sprinkle tops with nutmeg.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook 4 minutes on high. Remove and stir. Cook 4 more minutes on high. Add 1 tablespoon butter and mix, cook 2 more minutes on high. Remove and immediately add 1 teaspoon soda. Stir well and pour onto well buttered cookie sheet. Spread thin. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: fudge
directions: Cook oleo, sugar, milk and salt; bring to boil.
Stir all the time; boil 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows and chips; pour into greased pan!
Chill and cut into squares.

title: italian custard toast
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bread.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a generously buttered 8 by 8-inch baking dish.
Add bread; top with remaining egg mixture.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: five cup salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl; toss lightly. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake in pie dish at 375° until warm (about 15 minutes).
Serve with crackers.

title: sand art brownies
directions: Stir with fork until moistened. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave easy rice pudding
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure or casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Cook uncovered, 6 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring occasionally during last half of cooking time.
Serve warm or cool.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with sliced onions.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over chops. Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes, or until chops are tender. Remove chops to platter and spoon sauce over chops.
Serve with a smile.

title: quick pizzas
directions: Split muffins; spread with spoonful of pizza sauce.
Top with 2 or 3 pepperoni slices and cover with cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add water and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until okra is tender.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix milk and water and combine with eggs.
Add vanilla and pour into greased custard cups or a baking dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of custard.
Place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour until custard is set.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet (or 2 small ones); set aside. Combine syrup, sugar and peanuts in heavy iron skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until syrup turns light brown. Remove from heat.
Add soda and beat very well (soda will foam). Pour onto greased cookie sheet as thin as possible.
Cool and break into pieces.
Serves 3 to 4 grandchildren.

title: no peekie stew
directions: Mix first four ingredients well in a 3-quart Dutch oven or casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles, toss with butter.
Place on a large serving dish or platter and top with the stew.

title: margaritas
directions: Mix with ice and enjoy!

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remainder and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: bread dough sculpture
directions: Mix well.
Divide into 4 parts and flatten each ball.
Make the figures you want.
Lay figures on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
When cool, paint with acrylic paints and glue pieces of fabric or trim, if you desire.
Add a coat of clear varnish over all bread parts.
Paper clips make a good hanger and can be inserted before baking.

title: peanut drop cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla and water.
Add dry ingredients.
On greased cookie sheet, drop spoonfuls of cookie dough.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of peanut butter on top of each and another 1/2 teaspoon of cookie dough as top layer. Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add cranberry sauce and mix well. Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour half mixture in dish and chill. Cover with sour cream and put other half of jello mixture on top.

title: icy walnut balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan (do not pat down).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir occasionally, until crumbs are toasted and golden brown.
Cool; set aside.
In same mixing bowl, combine milk, extract and powdered sugar.
Stir in dates and remaining walnuts.
Drop by scant teaspoon into cooled crumbs; shape into balls, rolling to coat.
Store in refrigerator.
Bake at 400°.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: ham soup
directions: Cook cabbage, ham and onion in pot filled with water and ketchup.
Cook until cabbage is done and take ham off bone. Meanwhile, cook potatoes until done (not overdone).
Cut up and add to soup.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add nuts.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes until nuts are heated through.
Mix sugar, spices and salt.
Add nuts and toss until all sugar mixture coats nuts.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Stir in oats, nuts and coconut; mix well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drop from teaspoon and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shells (graham cracker).
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and onion.
Place on serving platter.
Top with 1/2 bottle Heinz chili sauce and crab meat.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Put rice in greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rice.
Lay raw chicken breasts over top and add rest of dry onion soup.
Bake, covered with foil, at 325° for 2 hours.
The last 1/2 hour, uncover.

title: hummus tahini
directions: Combine chickpeas, warm water, olive oil and juice of 1 lemon in the bowl of food processor with a steel blade.
Process until smooth and creamy.
Pause once or twice to scrape sides of bowl. Add garlic, salt, cumin seed and pepper to taste and process to blend.
Taste and correct seasonings.
Add more lemon juice to taste.
Scrape into a storage container.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: mac's wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
It will look watery but that's okay.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use cake tester at 35 to 37 minutes to be sure cake is not overcooked as it will be dry and not as moist tasting.
Cool on cooling rack.
Frost or can use Cool Whip as a topping on cake.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Crush graham crackers.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Shape, wrap in foil and put back in cracker box.

title: chicken and dressing for senior citizens day at o.p.v.
directions: In a 15-gallon pot, place chicken and about 10 gallons of water.
Cook until chickens are tender.
Let cool and debone. Have cornbread cooked.
You will need at least a 15 gallon pot to mix the dressing.

title: tea cakes(plain)
directions: Flavor to taste.
Roll thin and bake in a low oven (275° to 300°).

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and milk; mix well.
Add ground beef, ground pork and cooked rice; beat together with a fork.
Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water for 3 minutes or just until limp; drain.
Heavy center vein of leaf may be slit about 2 1/2 inches.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix and beat ingredients for about 4 minutes.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; stir well.
Add vegetables.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Use a slotted spoon to serve slaw.
Yields 6 servings.

title: microwave super tuna casserole
directions: Unwrap cream cheese and place in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole; microwave 30 seconds until cheese softens. Add soup and stir well.
Fold in rice, tuna, mushrooms, onions, pimentos and pepper; cover.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes or until heated through. Let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on box. Cool. Crumble cornbread and mix with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup,
milk
and
pepper.
Alternate
layers of potatoes, onions, cheese
and
soup.
Put
mixture in buttered 2 1/2 quart shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: nutty oven-fried chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine biscuit mix, pecans and seasonings; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; coat generously with pecan mixture.
Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until juices run clear.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy tamale bake
directions: Unwrap tamales and arrange in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Spread tamale sauce on top.
Pour beans over tamales.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and onions. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: Combine egg white and water; add nuts and mix well.
Add spices and sugar; mix well.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Double 6 times for 2 gallons of peanuts.

title: zucchini-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Saute diced zucchini in margarine.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and hamburger.
Place in 2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon onto wax paper.
Beat sugar, butter or margarine in medium size bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Stir in mincemeat by hand, then add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip. Cool for 15 minutes in the pan and cut into squares.
Leave in pan and wrap tightly in aluminum foil. Can be stored up to 2 weeks.

title: snickers bar cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a food processor, grind cookies into fine crumbs.
Add butter; process until well blended.
Press into bottom and about 1 inch up sides of a 9 1/2 or 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: sweet taste of chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken in greased baking dish. Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken. I cook mine in an electric frypan and let it simmer for about 1 hour. This can be cooked in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add honey and vanilla.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture alternately with oil.
Add zucchini, nuts and coconut (add 2 tablespoons flour to nuts before adding).
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: skillet chicken stew
directions: In large electric skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and turn heat to high.
Add chicken and cook about 15 minutes, turning to brown on all sides.
Push chicken to one side of skillet.
Add onion and celery and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cut chicken as if for frying.
Line roaster with foil.
Set oven to 500°.
Salt and pepper the chicken.
Dip in sauce and place in pan with remaining sauce.
Cover over all with the foil. Cover the roaster.
Cook 15 minutes at 500°, then lower to 350° and cook 1 1/4 hours or longer.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, oil, eggs and water together.
Add coconut, nuts and strawberries; mix well.
Bake in a tube pan for about 1 hour at 325° or until done.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef; add other ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: speck and dicken
directions: Mix rye flour, white flour and eggs together.
Salt and sugar to taste and add the soda.
Mix together with enough buttermilk to make a medium thin batter.
Part sour cream will improve the batter.
Fry the sausage and bacon.
Cut bacon in small pieces and slice sausage in thin pieces.
Heat skillet, preferably an iron skillet, until hot (well greased).
Pour in pancake and skin of sausage and bacon.
Turn when brown and brown the other side. Continue until batter is used completely.

title: baked string beans(fagiolini al forno)
directions: Drain string beans
in colander; set aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter
and
saute
onion.
When onion is tender but not brown, add beans and saute for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and toss the breadcrumbs in with the bean mixture.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30
to
40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
This is a wonderful dish to have for a buffet table, always a hit.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Place butter and brown sugar in skillet. Let butter melt, place pineapple slices on mixture.
Place a maraschino cherry in center of slices.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix sour cream, pineapple and pudding mix.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: steak slices with horseradish cream
directions: Slice steak into 5-inch wide strips. Combine soy sauce and wine in shallow dish. Add steak and marinate in refrigerator 24 hours. Brush steak with oil and broil without rack 6-inches from heat for 1 minute on each side. Then broil 5 minutes each side. Allow steak to cool. Brush with marinade juices and refrigerate. When cold, cut into very thin diagonal slices. Serve with toothpicks for dipping into horseradish cream.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk and 1 cup of the cheese.
Cook until the cheese is melted on low heat.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Roll the cut up chicken into the crescent rolls and place them on top of the soup-cheese mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with the rest of the cheese and garnish with parsley and parsley flakes.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
(This freezes well after baking and can be reheated in the microwave.)

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift flour, meal, salt and baking powder together.
Add egg and milk.
Mix well.
Add chopped onion.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: easy peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in pan.
Boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until candy begins to thicken.
(This stirring is important.) Pour into buttered dish.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift together into a mixing bowl the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in soft butter until particles are fine.
Add egg, cream and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Dough may be refrigerated or frozen, if desired.
Roll out on floured pastry cloth or board to 1/4-inch thickness (or whatever works for you).
Cut into desired shapes.
Slightly grease cookie sheets.
You can put some decorations, i.e., cherries, sprinkles, sugar, before baking.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes or until "delicately brown."
Cool before decorating.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot 'n sweet mustard
directions: Combine dry mustard and vinegar; let set 30 minutes.
Mix in all other ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs and dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add nuts and prunes.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: summer potato casserole
