directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes; slice.	Combine cheese, mayonnaise and onion; gently stir into potatoes.
Place in a greased casserole and top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Arrange cookie dough in a round pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Cream remaining ingredients together and spread over crust.
Arrange thinly sliced fruit over cream cheese mixture (strawberries, crushed pineapple, blueberries, mandarin oranges and kiwi work well).

title: sunshine granola
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir oil and honey together. Pour over dry mixture, stirring well.
Spread mixture on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and break into large pieces.
Combine pieces with remaining ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
about 12 cups.

title: microwave nuts and bolts party mix
directions: Heat margarine in 3-quart bowl 1 1/2 minutes until melted. Stir in Worcestershire, garlic and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool before serving or storing.

title: tex mex dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch or large platter, layer the following: bean dip and guacamole.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning.
Layer on top of guacamole. Top with olives, tomatoes, lettuce and end with cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with taco chips and salsa.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook ditalini or macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in a skillet or wok, stir-fry chicken in hot oil about 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add green pepper, onion, cumin and red pepper.
Cook and stir 3 minutes longer, adding more oil, if necessary.
Stir in drained pasta, corn and salt.
Cover and cook 2 minutes more or until hot.
Stir in tomatoes; sprinkle edge of skillet with cheese.
Cover; heat 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook 2 to 3 cups of carrots in salted water until tender. Combine all ingredients, cook until thickened.
Pour over carrots and reheat.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute shrimp in 5 tablespoons butter until pink.
Add garlic, shallots and pepper.
When shrimp is done (4 to 5 minutes, until barely transparent), add remaining butter.
As it melts, stir in wine slowly, mixing until it emulsifies.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.
Can be cut in half for two.

title: punch mix
directions: In large punch bowl, pour in Kool-Aid, all juices and ginger ale.
Stir to mix.
Add ice cream and stir before serving.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream mix
directions: Mix together and put in ice cream churn.

title: 15 minute midget meat loaves
directions: Combine and mix well.
Add to this mixture one pound of ground beef.
Pack mixture into eight 3-inch or ten 2 1/2-inch up, ungreased muffin pans.
Cover with remaining tomato paste or 1/3 cup catsup.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes. Recipe serves 4 to 5 persons.

title: mocha java
directions: Mix 2 heaping teaspoons of mix to one cup of hot water.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix diced chicken, sour cream and soup together; place in a baking dish.
Mix crackers, butter and poppy seed; sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and salt, mayonnaise and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar and blend well.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat.
Cut up into small pieces.
Add cut up carrots, potatoes, chopped onion and soup.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix well and pour in crust.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.
Sweet potatoes may be used instead of pumpkin.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Cook flour, sugar, butter
and	vinegar; add juice from pimento and cook until
thick.
Pour
over	the
following and blend together:
pimento, salad dressing and cheese.

title: chocolate frosting(layer cake size)
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch and sugar together, then add salt and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cut in half for loaf cake.
Makes a nice pudding-like frosting.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; boil in salted water until tender; drain off water.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake until puffy and bubbly; bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add grated cheese the final 5 minutes of baking.

title: tuna pate
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: hawaiian paradise pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Blend in pineapple, coconut, and nuts.
Add lemon juice last to set mixture like gelatin.
Pour mixture into pie shells and refrigerate.
You can sprinkle loose graham cracker crumbs or nuts on top, if desired.

title: black bean quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Spray large nonstick baking sheet with cooking spray. Place 2 tortillas on prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle each with half the cheese.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup, milk, tomatoes and chilies and onion together.
Next, use a little chicken broth in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Place a layer of tortillas, sauce mixture and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet dill slices
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine other ingredients in pot over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumber slices.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pack slices in hot jars, cover with syrup and seal at once.
Note:
Less salt can be used and vinegar can be cut with water if too strong.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: apricot date bars
directions: Cook apricots, dates, brown sugar and apricot juice until thick.
Cool slightly.
Mix into crumbs:
shortening, brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Place 1/2 the crumbs in greased pan.
Spread fruit filling over crumbs.
Put balance of crumbs over top of filling and pat down with hand or spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: angel pie
directions: Grease pie plate (very important).

title: chili dip #2
directions: Put cream cheese in bottom of casserole dish. Layer other ingredients on top in order. Microwave on High until bubbly. Serve with Doritos.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Combine rhubarb, sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Put this mixture in a square pan or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread crumb mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy applesauce cake wedges
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, margarine and egg in bowl.
Work until crumbly.
Spread half the mixture into greased 9-inch pan.
Top with applesauce.
To remaining crumbs add cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Spread over applesauce.
Cover completely.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost chopped broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in melted margarine for a few minutes.
Add broccoli, soup, rice and cheese. Place all of this into a casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain fat.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides.
Seal well.
Spoon sausage onto crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apple slices in ungreased 1 3/4-cup casserole.

Sprinkle water, lemon juice and cinnamon on apples. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle on apples. Bake, uncovered, until apples are tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Top with light cream or ice cream, if you like.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hobo chicken
directions: Place the pieces of chicken into pan or dish.
Place vegetable pieces around chicken.
Mix the soup and water together and pour over the chicken.
Tightly seal with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour, until tender.

title: americanized rouladen
directions: Lightly beat meat slices and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread with mustard.
Prepare Stove Top according to package and put 1 tablespoon on each rouladen slice.
Add 1 bacon slice and roll up meat, beginning with the most narrow part.
Secure with wooden picks or SS roasting spears.
Dust or roll in flour and brown in hot oil, turning often.
Remove from pan and prepare gravy (homemade or canned mix).
Return Rouladen into gravy and simmer 1 hour, turning once.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured 9 inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: mini b.l.t.'s
directions: Cut bread with empty baby bottle.
Brown in oven.
Mix mayo and Bac*Os together just to mix and hold together.
Slice tommie toe tomatoes and top.
Refrigerate.
Great party snack and pretty too.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and egg in bowl. Microwave 5 minutes on 50% power.
Stir.
Add chocolate chips and stir.
Microwave 5 minutes more on 50% power.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill (in freezer).
(Can use this without chocolate chips, also.)

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds. Serve on Bibb lettuce.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water until they are just tender, not soft.
Drain.
Pour tomato soup into pan; add sugar, vinegar and oil.
Simmer until hot and sugar is dissolved.
Add sliced onions and green pepper.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add the carrots and refrigerate.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp. Cook onion, pepper and garlic in margarine until tender. Blend in flour and seasonings. Add tomatoes, sauce and water. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. May add more water, if needed. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp changes color. Serve over rice.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend cheese and butter until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Bring to room temperature several hours before served. Use raw vegetables or chips.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
Put through cookie press using star plate.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Don't overcook or they will have an unpleasant taste.

title: chicken sauce
directions: Cook all day.
Put through a strainer.
Serve over chicken that has been boned, breaded and baked.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: In large
baking
pan,
cut
sausage
links
(keep them whole, do not slice, just separate from the ring).
Peel, wash and
slice potatoes
into
quarters.
Place
potatoes
around sausage.
Peel and
slice
onions into eighths.
Place around sausage.
If
you are
using
the
Italian tomatoes, break up tomatoes by
squeezing and
spread over sausage, potatoes and onions.
Add enough
water to cover the bottom of the pan and sprinkle the spices over all. Cover pan with foil and bake at 325° for 3/4
of
an
hour. Remove
the foil and bake for 1/2 hour, making sure
there is water or sauce at bottom of pan so potatoes won't stick.
Serves 4 to 6.
Accompany with a tossed green salad and French or Italian bread.

title: pumpkin pecan pie(quick, easy and good)
directions: This pie is always the hit of every family gathering for the Tye family.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil and place in chicken.
Mix together dressing, soup and preserves and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix in melted margarine.
Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir sauce into ground beef and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into the pot of spaghetti and mix.
Hand chop spaghetti and sauce mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix cheeses together and sprinkle on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick marinara sauce
directions: In a large sauce pan over medium heat add oil, garlic, red pepper.
When the garlic starts to sizzle add in the tomatoes and herbs.
Bring to a bubble and reduce the heat and let simmer 30-40 minutes.

title: chicago crunchy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, margarine, brown and regular sugars, egg, milk and vanilla in bowl until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with oil until mixture is thoroughly mixed. Stir in corn flakes, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on racks.

title: yummy walnuts
directions: Combine sugars, syrup and cream. Cook to a soft ball. Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Add walnuts.
Stir until they are well coated.
Turn out onto a well-greased pan. Separate.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix in a 1 gallon Ziploc bag until dough-like consistency. Roll out on waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Cut with cookie cutter and place on a cookie sheet.
Let dry, turning every few hours until dry (may take a few days).
Poke holes when wet for ribbon to hang with. Do not bake.

title: prairie fire dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine the beans, cheese, butter (if desired), onion, garlic, chili powder and hot pepper sauce. Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and dip is heated through. Serve with corn chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet melt margarine.
Add chopped onion and celery, saute until tender and transparent. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: chicken in an acorn
directions: Pound breasts until flat on both sides on a surface floured with all except 2 tablespoons of the flour.
Cut chicken into 1 x 1-inch pieces, dipping cut edges in the flour, reserving the leftover flour.
Marinate the chicken in the milk 1 1/2 hours in refrigerator.
Remove from milk.
Drain, reserving milk.
Dip in flour again.
Heat oil and brown chicken over medium heat about 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove chicken and drain.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons of the oil.
Add the reserved flour, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth.
Add reserved milk.
Cook until thickened. Add mushrooms, pimento, bell pepper and stuffing mix.
Add chicken, mixing well.
Stuff mixture into squash.
Bake in 375° oven, covered, about 50 minutes or until squash and chicken are tender.
Warm the Cran-Orange sauce.
Serve over the squash. Serves 4.

title: summer cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Slice onion in rings; slice bell pepper.
Put in large bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed to cucumber mixture.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Stir several times before refrigerating.
Keep refrigerated.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; discard soaking liquid.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato and cilantro.
Slow cook until beans are tender (slow cooker = 8 to 10 hours; simmer on stove for 3 hours). Garnish with tomato and cilantro.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup bones, onion, celery, salt and pepper in a pressure cooker on 10 pounds for 50 minutes (these bones are usually frozen).
After cooking bones, cut meat from bones and put back into pot, along with the remaining ingredients and sufficient water for juice.
Cook for another 10 minutes on 10 pounds pressure or until vegetables are tender.

title: vicky hall's meatballs
directions: Bake meatballs and drain.
Chop onion and slice green pepper. Put in crock-pot.
Stir in tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add pineapple chunks, meatballs, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.

title: cinnamon cream syrup
directions: Combine sugar, white corn syrup, water and cornstarch.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cinnamon and evaporated milk.
Delicious served over French toast or apple pancakes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain and wash beans.
Add green pepper and onion.
Marinate overnight in oil, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Brown meat; pour off excess fat.
Add next 4 ingredients. Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted boiling water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Place half of noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 of sauce and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: christmas crispies appetizers
directions: Using mixer, cream together cheese and margarine.
Add flour, pepper and Rice Krispies.
Hard to mix. Possibly you need to mix with your hands.
Form into balls and flatten.
Press fork in top once each way.
Bake in 350°
oven for 18 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Store tightly covered.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients until smooth. Chill for 30 minutes. Beat until stiff peaks form. Store in refrigerator.

title: beef pie
directions: Saute beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, milk, eggs and sauce.
Add 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Allow to cool 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine cocoa, 1 cup sugar, flour, salt and milk in double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Stir while cooking.
Stir in beaten egg yolks.
Cook 2 minutes and add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat the egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until mixture stands in peaks.
Spread on pie. Bake in oven at 300° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together soup, oil, salt, dill weed, sugar, cider vinegar and pepper.
Heat.
Then add onion, green pepper and carrots. Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix eggs, pie filling and almond flavoring together until well blended.
Add dry cake mix and stir until well mixed.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool on cake rack.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill in refrigerator before serving to allow flavors to blend.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Saute onion and garlic.
In a bowl, beat the eggs.
Add bread crumbs and spices.
Stir in cheese, parsley, onion and artichokes.
Turn into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then cut into squares.
Serve cold or reheat.

title: rice and chicken pie
directions: Cook rice for 7 minutes and set aside.
In skillet over medium heat, cook chicken in margarine.
Stir in seasoning mix and water. Cook, stirring often, until it thickens, about 3 to 4 minutes. Combine rice, 1/2 cup salsa, egg and 1 cup cheese.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle in 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with remaining cheese; let stand for 10 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with remaining salsa.

title: jen's bluefish
directions: Line rectangular Pyrex dish with aluminum foil.
Place bluefish fillets in it.
Combine mayonnaise, buttermilk and lemon juice.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes (approximately 1/2 hour).
Put under broiler for a few minutes.

title: grandma's cocoa cakes
directions: Using an electric mixer, cream butter.
Add sugar and cocoa; beat until creamy.
Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour with baking soda.
Add 1/2 cup flour mixture to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream; blend.
Alternate 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup sour cream, blending well after each addition, until all ingredients are used.
Bake in paper lined muffin tins at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan and bake for 12 minutes (or until lightly brown) at 350°. Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons oleo until soft.
Stir in flour and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli; add eggs.
Mix gently until blended; turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with remaining oleo.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat milk, marshmallows and candy in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows and candy are melted and blended. Refrigerate about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Beat whipping cream in chilled large bowl with electric mixer on high speed until soft peaks form. Fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate, uncovered, at least 8 hours, until set. Garnish with strawberry slices and mint leaves. Makes 12 servings.

title: cheesy chocolate cupcakes(they freeze well)
directions: Cream the cream cheese with egg and salt.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and beat with beater.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill well greased baking tins or use paper baking cups with chocolate batter 1/2 full. Spoon heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese batter on top of each. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20.

title: hot onion bread
directions: Slice bread diagonally, almost through.
Mix first 3 ingredients and spread between bread slices and on top.
Sprinkle bread with paprika and parsley flakes.
Wrap bread in foil, bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender, chop into bite size pieces.
Saute celery and onion in 1 1/2 Tbsp. margarine.
Mix with chicken, soup, chestnuts, mushrooms and mayo.
Pour into long rectangle baking dish.
Cover with crescent rolls to make crust. Top with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut drop cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift together with baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine butter and sugar, blending well. Add melted chocolate, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Fold in nuts. Drop by teaspoon on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bible school cookies
directions: Melt oleo and shortening. Add sugars and vanilla.
Cool.
Stir in eggs, water and oats.
Mix 1 cup flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to shortening mixture. Add remaining flour, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 25 dozen.
These freeze well.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Grind together, using coarse blade of grinder, the cabbage, onions, peppers, carrots and then add salt and mustard seed.
Let mixture stand for 2 hours.
Squeeze mixture well.
Then add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Cover mixture and let stand one hour or more.
Mix well and pack in hot jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: tuxedo brownies
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan make brownies according to package directions. Cool and top with jam, then raspberries.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: lone star fondue
directions: Cut bread in chunks and saute with butter and oil.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: summer asparagus
directions: Lightly steam trimmed asparagus approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine all the remaining items and chill.
Pour over asparagus immediately before serving.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan melt butter. Stir in dry pudding mixes and milk. Bring to boil for 1 minutes. Remove from heat. Beat in sugar. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour batter into 1 1/2 inch baking dish. Garnish with walnuts.

title: hash
directions: Stir all together.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring often. Leftovers are good for this.
May add more pepper to taste, also salt, if not seasoned enough.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all, except bananas, together.
Chill.
Add sliced bananas 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: apricot slush
directions: Mix tea, sugar and water altogether.
Add orange juice, lemonade and apricot brandy.
Freeze.
Use as needed.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter, add brown sugar, eggs, mandarin rind, mix well. Mix flour and baking soda together, add to butter mixture.
Mix in pecans.
Shape dough into long rolls about 2-inches wide.
Wrap in waxed paper, chill.
When ready to bake, slice 1/4-inch slices, place on cookie sheet, bake 350° 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookie dough rolls can be refrigerated for up to a month.
Makes 75 cookies.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix well. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: minted cucumbers and yogurt salad
directions: Combine dressing ingredients and chill.
Stir with cucumbers just before serving.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together in blender or by hand.
Makes 1 cup.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Roll nuts in	flour.	Sift
soda and salt into the remaining flour. Add flour
and buttermilk alternately.	Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: "plantation room" ham salad
directions: Put ham and bologna through meat grinder.
Cut up boiled eggs and Cheddar cheese into small pieces and add to ham and bologna. Add relish and mayonnaise and enjoy!

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Butter tops.

title: french silk wedges
directions: Combine sugar and butter, beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at least 2 minutes after each addition.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over crust.
Refrigerate at least eight hours before serving.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until set.

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Mix soda and yogurt in a bowl until it foams up.
Add immediately to flour and mix until fairly smooth.
Add a little water if too stiff.
Fry in a small amount of safflower oil (or similar).
Good for dieters.
Serve with applesauce, or brown sugar, for lower calories.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Spread immediately with peanut butter (a thin layer). Cool in refrigerator.
Melt a large Hershey bar or 6 regular bars in a double boiler; spread evenly over the cake.
Best kept in the refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon.
Drain.
Mix ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: triple threat!(chocolate heaven. . .and easy!)
directions: Use a big pot!
Cook chocolate pudding according to directions.
When it starts to thicken, pour in cake mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Put in oven and bake as instructed on cake mix box.
A zillion calories per serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and sprouts and put into baking dish.
Add onion and soup. Mix well. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Top with French onion rings for last 10 minutes.

title: almond meringue torte
directions: In mixer bowl,	cream the 1/2 cup sugar and shortening. Add egg yolks,	one
at
a time, beating well after each addition. Stir
in
milk
and
vanilla
extract.
Combine
flour, baking powder and	1/4
teaspoon
salt; add to creamed mixture and beat until
smooth.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch cake pans. Beat egg whites
with
pinch of salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Beat
in
cup
sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff, glossy peaks form.
Divide meringue between pans, spreading over
batter.
Sprinkle
with
almonds
and 1 tablespoon sugar mixed with the cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto rack to cool.	Using second rack, turn again so meringue is right side up.
Save any almonds that may fall off for
garnish. No	more
than 6 hours before serving, place 1 layer,
meringue side
up,
on serving plate.
Spread with
3/4 of sweetened whipped cream flavored with vanilla and fruit.
Top
with remaining layer, meringue side up;	garnish with remaining cream and more fruit.
Serves 10 to 16.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Drain and reserve pineapple juice.
Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Add pineapple and pour into 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Top with miniature marshmallows and let congeal.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Can be garnished with chopped nuts or cherries, if desired.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Spray pan with Pam. Bake.
When done poke holes in cake.
Pour milk over cake.
Mix Cool Whip, coconut and vanilla.
Pour over cake.
Chill overnight.

title: diet punch
directions: Chill the Kool-Aid, pineapple juice and ginger ale separately. Mix in punch bowl just before serving.

title: coconut macaroon cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add coconut flavoring and coconut last.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour (350°).
Leave in pan to cool.
While cake is still warm, mix 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Boil 1 minute and add 1 1/2 teaspoons coconut flavoring.
Punch holes in cake and pour sugar mixture over cake.
Can put powdered sugar frosting on cake when cool, if desired.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine boiling water, lemon jello and cider vinegar.
When cool, add the cream cheese blended with mayonnaise.
Add celery, green pepper, eggs and corned beef.
Pour into lightly oiled 8 x 10-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: goober glazed chicken
directions: Sprinkle salt, garlic salt and pepper over chicken.
Place peanut oil in skillet and brown chicken strips until done.
Dip in honey mustard mixture.
Roll in chopped peanuts.
Serve on a bed of fried rice.
Garnish with red bell pepper, spring onions and parsley.

title: "buck-eye" balls
directions: Mix and roll into
balls
the first 4 ingredients.
Put on cookie sheet and
chill.
Melt
chocolate
chips
in double boiler with paraffin.
Dip balls in this mixture and return to cookie sheet.

title: turkey curry (leftovers) or any fresh meat
directions: Cut the meat into cubes and fry until golden brown in margarine.
If using leftovers, this will only take a few minutes; with fresh meat, you should allow a longer time for cooking.
Drain well.
Put into a casserole dish.
Fry chopped onions and apples and add to meat.
Fry curry powder very well.
Fry flour 2 to 3 minutes.
Gradually add stock; mix and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Add seasoning, raisins, tomatoes, etc., and pour over meat.
Cover casserole and cook gently in a moderately hot oven at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: ground pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add cinnamon; fold in ground pecans.
Set aside 6 tablespoons of egg whites with sugar before adding cinnamon.
Top each cookie with a small amount.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Dropping by teaspoon makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir tomato sauce and seasonings into meat mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles 3 to 5 minutes; drain and combine with sour cream.
Start with noodles and alternate layers of noodles, meat and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle cheese on top and cook for additional 15 minutes.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: Saute the beef, celery, onion, green pepper and garlic until tender.
Add water, tomato paste and remaining ingredients, except the beans.
Reserve 1 cup of sauce for Biscuits.
Add beans and simmer.
Prepare Biscuits.

title: theta "tea cup" fruit cobbler
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or pan.
Spread pie filling in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spread dry cake mix over filling.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Melt margarine and pour over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in deep 9-inch round skillet or baking pan.
Add brown sugar.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cut pineapple in half and arrange with cherries in bottom and around sides of pan.
Prepare cake mix.
Fill prepared pan 3/4 full and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While cake is hot, run knife around cake edge and invert cake on serving plate.
(May use leftover batter for cupcakes.)

title: apple and raisin salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the apples, pineapple tidbits, celery, pecans and raisins. In a smaller bowl, mix together the sour cream, salad dressing, sugar and orange juice. Pour over first mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until chilled. Toss again just before serving.

title: grandma's funeral salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl:
lettuce, celery, onion, cauliflower, cucumber, tomatoes, pepper and carrot on top.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Spread 1/2 of batter into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Spread 1/2 of chocolate chips over batter, then add 1/2 of sugar, cinnamon mixture.
Repeat with batter, chocolate chips and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 1930's depression okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onions and add the okra.
Cook until okra is blended, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Stir and simmer until okra is done.
A small amount of flour may be added for thickness; either flour okra before adding to onions or while okra and tomatoes are simmering.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: beef ole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add chili powder, taco mix, tomato sauce and water.
Cook over moderate heat about 8 minutes.
Pour over Fritos on plate and serve.
Cover with chopped lettuce, onions, tomatoes, olives, grated cheese and salsa, if desired.
Serve Ranch Style beans on the side, if desired.

title: freida's chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk until sugar dissolves and add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips until dissolved.
Add oats, coconut and walnuts.
Stir until well coated and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool until firm.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix in large bowl with pineapple. Add Cool Whip, marshmallows, and nuts. Blend well. Chill before serving.

title: sour milk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Work in Crisco and sour milk.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Makes 8 biscuits.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Stir until mixed well.
Let stand covered in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Beat together sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into sugar and egg mixture.
Thoroughly stir in melted chocolate and margarine; add nuts.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Cook meat and brown slightly.
Add peppers and onions.
Then add garlic, beans, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: russian rocks(this is a good christmas cookie!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add soda and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to flour and blend well.
Add pecans and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees about 15 minutes.

title: lendburg's pie
directions: Crumble saltines in bottom of 8-inch aluminum pie pan (this is crust).
Put dates and pecans on crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in 1 cup sugar and add the flavoring.
Pour this mixture onto pecans and dates.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine first four ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat well and stir in chocolate chips; set aside.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Combine turkey, noodles, and peas in a 2 qt. buttered casserole dish.
Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in a saucepan.
Saute onion and mushrooms; blend in soup, milk, seasonings.
Pour soup mixture over meat; top with shredded cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20-30 minutes.

title: black walnut delight cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Mix well. Add walnuts.
Blend just enough to blend well.
Add beaten egg whites.
Fold into batter.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn out and let cool.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken so it will fit into covered pan.
Add desired salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Cook until done.
Let cool and take chicken off bones.
Save broth.
Saute pepper and onion in margarine in large saucepan.
Do not brown.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth (the spaghetti will absorb most of the broth but do not drain).
In the large saucepan with pepper and onion, add cubed cheese, chicken and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix lightly until cheese melts.
Mix in peas.
Pour sauce over spaghetti.
Pour into 2 casserole dishes.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes. This freezes well.
Do not reheat in microwave.

title: low-fat molasses cookies
directions: In food processor with metal blade, combine prunes and hot water.
Cover; process approximately 2 to 3 minutes or until nicely pureed.
In a big bowl, put the prune mixture, 1 cup sugar, molasses and egg whites.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves and mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks until light and fluffy.
Slowly add 1/2 of the sugar, beating well.
Add vanilla; gently fold in flour mixture, using water to lighten the batter.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add remaining sugar gradually.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Gently fold mixture into egg whites.
Spread in a large jelly roll pan that has been greased and lined with waxed or parchment paper.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Peel paper off.
Let cool slightly and roll up.

title: onion bread
directions: Bring 2 cups water to boiling in saucepan; add soup mix and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sugar, salt, cheese and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water in large bowl; stir to dissolve.
Stir in onion soup mixture and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed, scraping the bowl occasionally, 2 minutes or by hand until batter sheets from spoon.
Mix in remaining flour, a little at a time, first with spoon and then with hands, until dough leaves the sides of bowl.
Dough will be moderately stiff.

title: mom schroeder's apple butter
directions: Bake at 300° in oven.
Cook to desired thickness.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: mrs. e.c.e. pecan pie
directions: In unbaked pie crust, pour 1 cup pecans.
Using mixer or blender, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over pecans in crust.
Bake for full 50 minutes at 350°.

title: beefy baked bean casserole
directions: Combine meat, bell pepper and onion; brown and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: red salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1/3 cup hot water. Add crushed pineapple, nuts and crushed bananas. Add the frozen strawberries. Mix and let congeal. Spread the sour cream, beaten at room temperature, over first layer.

title: old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: In a large saucepan combine granulated sugar, water and light corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally to 238° (soft ball stage in cold water).
Stir in peanuts.
Continue to cook and stir to 285° (hard cracking stage).
Quickly stir in butter and baking soda.
Pour and spread thin on 2 greased baking sheets.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes about 1 pound peanut brittle.
We've been making this candy since 1974.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Heat oil in skillet. Put in vegetables and stir-fry.
Then add chicken broth.
Make thickening with cornstarch and slowly pour into skillet and stir. Then add chicken, bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Rack height second to lowest level.
Using big aluminum roasting pan or broiler, wrap outside of pan in heavy-duty foil and crunch down around top.
Put 1-inch of water in roasting pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients:
crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press in spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese and add condensed milk.
Beat slowly until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix 1/2 cup mini chips with flour and then swirl into mixture.
Pour mixture on crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chips on top. Bake 1 hour until center is set.
When done, ease foil away from pan.
Set on a rack; cool to room temperature.
Run knife around the pan and release.
Refrigerate.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Mix with the other 4 ingredients.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot ham and potatoes
directions: In crock-pot, layer half the ham, potatoes and onion. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and half the cheese.
Repeat layers; then spoon soup over top.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: tzimmes
directions: Peel and cut vegetables into chunks and cook in water covered with salt until almost done.
Add prunes through lemon juice covering until cooked.
Combine the last two ingredients and stir into the vegetable liquid to thicken.
Serves 6.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine and beat thoroughly sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamy mixture.
Add cereal, oatmeal and coconut. Roll into balls and flatten with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar, milk and dates until it forms a soft ball (238°). Remove from heat and add nuts and stir until hard enough to form a ball.
Pour mixture onto a greased tea towel and form into a loaf shape.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: beefy macaroni skillet
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat to low, cook until heated thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: beef, beer and onions
directions: Cut fat from meat and slice into strips.
Heat oil in a large frying pan and cook meat until evenly browned.
Remove meat from frying pan and set aside.
Add onions to fat in pan and cook over medium heat until soft, about 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Stir in garlic and season with salt and pepper.
Continue to cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Arrange half of browned meat in bottom of two-quart casserole.
Spread with half of the onions.
Repeat layers.
Add consomme and sugar to frying pan, stirring to dissolve sugar. Bring to boil.
Add spices and pour over meat.
Pour in beer until meat is covered.

title: frozen cranberry salad(or dessert)
directions: Cream the cream cheese with sugar; add cranberries, pineapple and walnuts.
Mix together thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Pour into a large Pyrex dish (9 x 13-inch) or salad mold.
Freeze about 8 hours.
Let sit at room temperature a few minutes before serving.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Bring 4 cups water to boil, adding salt to taste.
Add macaroni to boiling water; cook until tender.
Pour in strainer to drain all water, then place in pot.
Add cheese and eggs immediately.
Mix ingredients to melt cheese.
Add pepper and additional
salt, if needed; blend well.
Pour in 1.5 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese with mixer; gradually add milk and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: hallelujah chicken
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream in mixing bowl. Stir in cooked chicken.
Place chicken mixture in 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
For topping, melt butter, then add Waverly cracker crumbs and poppy seed.
Place topping onto chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: italian beef
directions: Sprinkle roast with spices (generous amount) on all sides.
Cut onion and place in crock-pot with beef.
Pour water into crock-pot and cover.
Cook overnight and all next day.
Use a fork to break up beef during next day.
Serve on french rolls with sauce of choice and a slice of Swiss.
Yum!

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick with a fork.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: roll no-crust chicken pie
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit the baking powder.
Spray pan or baking dish that is 2-inches deep.
Place chicken in dish and pour melted butter over it.
Boil 1 3/4 cups chicken broth and add cubes.
Mix dry ingredients; add milk and blend until smooth. Pour this over chicken.
Into broth with cubes, add soup.
Have boiling hot, pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: christmas ornaments you can eat
directions: Stir in flour a little at a time until dough is no longer sticky.
Knead about five minutes on waxed paper.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 25 minutes.
Fashion into Christmas shapes:
bell, tree, star, Santa, etc.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: burger stroganoff
directions: Prepare burger and onions together, set aside.
In large heavy pot pour cooking oil, flour, salt and pepper to season. There needs to be enough oil so the flour is not crumbly but smooth.
Stir continuously until brown.
Add broth and possibly water until you get a gravy thickness but not too thick.
Add burger and onions to gravy mixture, combining well, then add sour cream slowly, stirring continuously.
Serve on top of cooked egg noodles, rice or scalloped potatoes.
You may use stew beef instead of burger.
You also can add cooked mushrooms.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening with two knives or pastry blender until coarse textured.
Add well beaten egg with 1/2 cup water and the salt.
Roll into ball.
Divide into 4 portions.
(Can be put in pie tin and frozen, if desired.)
Roll one portion for prebaked crust for cream or lemon pies.
Prick with fork before baking in a 375° oven until nicely browned.
Cool and pour in desired filling.

title: corn pudding
directions: Lightly grease a 7-inch baking dish with oil.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat the eggs and evaporated milk together.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together in a small bowl.
Slowly add to egg mixture. Beat until blended.
Fold in corn, salt and pepper.
Put in pan and dot with oleo.
Bake until pudding is set and golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Grate 4 cups carrots.
Set oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix butter and sugar at high speed until light and fluffy.
At low speed, add flour mixture, 1/4 at a time, along with eggs, lemon and orange peels (optional) and juices.
Beat until smooth.
With a wooden spoon, fold in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Bake 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: In a large skillet, add Wesson oil.
Let skillet get hot. Flour the chicken; salt and pepper to taste.
Brown well on both sides until golden brown.
Bring broth to a boil.
Add rice and stir until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well. Bring white vinegar and sugar to a boil; pour over mixed vegetables. Let marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: velvet salad
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Pour in bowl. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight for best results.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Finely chop onions and lightly saute.
Mix together onions, bite-size chicken pieces, grated cheese, spices, mashed Rotel tomatoes, and chicken soup.
Cut tortillas in quarters.
Layer in shallow pan as follows:
1 qt chicken mixture, 60 tortilla quarters, 2 qt chicken mixture, 60 tortilla quarters, 3 qt chicken mixture.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.
Remove from the oven and top each pan with 1/2 lb grated cheese.
Continue baking for 5 more minutes.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Pound chicken into 1/4-inch thickness and cut into strips. Heat oil in large skillet until hot.
Dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry over medium heat 5 minutes per side or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix and flavor cake mix, flour, oil, water and egg.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheet a few minutes before removing.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Add a little water and cook for 10 minutes.
Drain it and mash it up.
Add remainder of ingredients. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1 1/2 cups grated cheese and 1 1/2 cups buttered crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Fry mushrooms, celery, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper in 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and milk. Pour mixture over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: old fashion praline candy
directions: Mix sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in a 3 1/2-quart saucepan. Cook over high heat to 210° on a candy thermometer, about 5 minutes. Stir frequently, being sure to scrape the bottom of the pan. Add the butter or margarine and pecans. Stir constantly, scraping the bottom and sides of the pan while cooking over medium heat. It should read 234° on candy thermometer (or test it for soft-ball stage). This means drop a little mixture in a glass of water to form a soft ball. Remove from heat and cool for about 2 minutes. Using a spoon, beat until thick and creamy. Then drop a tablespoon mixture on waxed paper or foil. Makes about 20.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind up green tomatoes, red peppers and green peppers in a bowl; add salt.
Let stand for 30 minutes; drain.
Add water and cook until dry or tender; cool.
Mix the sugar, flour, mustard, sweet pickles, cream, vinegar and eggs together, then cook all of this until thick.
Add the peppers and tomatoes that have cooled. Put in jars and refrigerate or seal while hot.

title: aggie salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients well together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill until set.

title: blueberry upside-down coffee cake batter
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and egg.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Set aside.

title: honey-oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix milk, oil, egg and honey.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Blend until moistened.
Bake in greased muffin tins 15 to 18 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen.
Serve warm.
Can be frozen.

title: teriyaki steak(serves 4)
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, honey, vinegar, onions, garlic and ginger.
Pour over steak and marinate at least 6 hours, 24 hours in refrigerator, turning several times.
Cover with plastic wrap.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Combine with stuffing mix and broth in bowl; mix well.
Layer 1/2 the mixture and chicken in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix soup and sour cream in bowl; pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yum yum bars
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt the butter.
Tip pan side by side to have butter on both sides of pan.
Add cracker crumbs mix and pat out for crust.
Add evenly over the crust as given: coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and pecan meats.
Drizzle milk over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut as desired.

title: ground veal sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make patties.
Extra patties can be frozen.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Use sauce for cake while still hot.

title: curried chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Mix brown mustard with curry powder.
Add	1/2
cup
corn	syrup and mix.	Place browned chicken in microwave
dish	and
cover with curry mixture.	Cook on Medium
power
for
5 minutes.
Turn chicken to baste and cook for an additional 5 minutes on Medium power.

title: caramel sauce
directions: In large heavy skillet, heat sugar over very low heat.
Stir constantly until melted and light golden brown.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in 1 cup hot water; bring to boiling point. Reduce heat and simmer until mixture thickens slightly or reaches 228° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Let cool.
Serve as a dressing over dessert.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Mix the sugar, salad oil, vinegar and salt in a jar and when well mixed pour over the beans, pepper and onions which were combined in a large bowl.
Marinate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Brown bacon and remove.
Add water.
Cut cabbage in bite size pieces.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: microwave green peas with celery and ripe olives
directions: Place celery in melted butter in a deep 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole.
Heat, covered, on full power 3 minutes.
Add peas; cover and heat on full power an additional 4 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in olives and seasonings; heat, covered, on full power 2 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in 350° oven until warm and bubbly.
"Great dip for crackers."

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add sugar, syrups, salt, vanilla and melted butter.
Line pie crust with pecans and pour filling over the nuts.
Bake slowly in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and roll in pecans.

title: shrimp chilli bites
directions: Saute shrimp in a little oil until pink.
Drain and cool. Sift all dry ingredients.
Add pounded green chilli peppers, onion and chopped coriander.
Add shrimp and mix into a stiff batter. Deep fry in oil until brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.

title: miracle pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with fork or pastry cutter until coarse texture.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg and remaining ingredients.
Combine 2 mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Mold dough into 3 or 4 balls.
Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.
I roll these and put in pie pans and freeze to use as needed.

title: capirotada (mexican bread pudding)
directions: In small saucepan, combine raisins, juice, sugar, cinnamon, zest and nutmeg.
Bring ingredients to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
In a large bowl, mix bread and raisins mixture by hand.
Add 2 cups of the shredded cheese and walnuts. Toss.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with cream.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and layer ingredients in order.
Pour tomatoes over mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Mix well and add flour, butter, milk and vanilla. Mix well and add pecans.
Blend well; bake until brown (middle should not be shaky) at 350°.

title: prisnits
directions: Brown bacon slightly in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients well. Pour into skillet.
Stir bacon into mixture.
Cover pan. Bake in oven for 3/4 to 1 hour at 350° or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Do not overcook.
Cut in approximately 2-inch squares.
Best when eaten warm, but also good cold.
Place leftovers in refrigerator.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Place 6 slices of bread on bottom of 12 x 8 inch baking dish. Cover with 1 c. cheddar cheese and ham and remaining bread slices, cut in 1/2, diagonally.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in milk and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: shortbread
directions: Beat butter until it appears whipped looking.
Mix in flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix in confectioners sugar and cornstarch.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan until even.
Poke with fork every inch in rows.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until golden brown.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Chill until set at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fruit.

title: polynesian pork chops
directions: Preheat broiler. Place pork chops on broiler pan; broil 4 to 5 inches from heat, approximately 8 minutes. Turn chops and broil 6 minutes more.

title: raisin cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups of flour and yeast.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Blend together in a saucepan, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Stir in water and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and has thickened slightly, (8 to 10 minutes). Stir in butter, vanilla and lemon juice. Set aside. Wash and peel tart apples; slice to make 4 cups. Arrange apple slices in a greased 9-inch square pan, which is at least 2 inches deep. Pour sauce over the apples. Prepare Sweet Drop Biscuit dough, (recipe in bread section.), and drop from a spoon over fruit mixture. Do not stir. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve warm, plain or with whipped cream or ice cream. This makes 6 servings.

title: ron's favorite cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese.
Add flour and mix well. Shape into 24 balls.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix chopped olives, cream cheese and onion dip together. Spread evenly on top of each ham/cheese slice.
Roll up and chill overnight.
Slice into bite-size pieces.
Serve with crackers or Triscuits.

title: butter mochi
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.	Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan
or
3 (5 x 7 1/2-inch) foil pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs and pumpkin. In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients; alternately add dry ingredients and water to the sugar mixture. Pour into 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and chill.
Form into balls or rolls.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley to taste.
Can be frozen or will keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 weeks.

title: black forest pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip on bottom of crust.
Combine milk and pudding mix in bowl.
Blend with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over Cool Whip in crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Cover with cherry pie filling. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Fry tortillas one at a time in 2 tablespoons oil in medium skillet 5 seconds on each side or until softened.
Add additional oil if necessary.
Drain on paper towels. Place a heaping 1/2 cup of chicken mixture on each tortilla and roll up.
Place seam side down in baking dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning.
Chop the onion and pepper.
Stir in hamburger.
Stir in pintos, cheese and Catalina dressing.
Put lettuce and chips in bowl. Put hamburger mixture over or eat alone with crackers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add marshmallow cream to softened cream cheese and add dash of ginger.
Stir until fluffy.
Serve with fruit.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Make pudding according to directions on the box.
Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Place, filling side up, in bottom of long dish or pan.
Spread pudding mixture on top of Twinkies.
Layer bananas and strawberries on top of the pudding and top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with sliced or whole strawberries.

title: festive holiday jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water and ice cubes; follow instructions on box.
Place in refrigerator until half jelled; do not overfreeze. Remove; add sour cream with electric mixer.
Beat until sour cream and Jell-O are thoroughly mixed.
Drain pineapple until all juice is gone.
Add pineapple to mixture and nuts.
Put into bowl. Garnish with split cherries.
Chill until set.

title: ham and barley soup
directions: Cook ingredients 1 hour, then add carrots and potatoes (as many as you want).
To thicken your soup add 2 tablespoons of flour with water, then add 1 tablespoon Gravy Master.
Cook 1 cup of barley by itself for about 1/2 hour, then add it to your soup. Serve with buttered bread.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Whip cream; drain pineapple and add to cream, folding in gently.
Add marshmallows by folding in.
Chill for 2 or more hours before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bacon-horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crisp, raw vegetables.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: green bean casserole(yields 10 to 15 servings)
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, onion and cheese together.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer beans, egg mixture and onion rings, ending with onion rings.
Add milk, if needed.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: country apples - crock-pot style
directions: Peel, slice and coat apples with flour and 1/3 cup sugar. Stir in the raisins, cinnamon and oatmeal.
Pour 1 cup water into crock-pot.
Add apple mix.
Pour melted butter over apples and then brown sugar.
Cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 6.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into well-greased small muffin tins. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain the beans well.
Add the sugars, liquid smoke, tomato sauce, onions and bell peppers.
Top with bacon or turkey bacon. Bake about 20 to 30 minutes.
Keeps well; can be frozen.

title: grandma's butter roll
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside. Make the biscuit dough by sifting flour into a large bowl.
Work in shortening.
Add milk and egg.
Add sugar.
Knead the dough until its firm.
Pinch off an egg size lump and roll it out on a floured piece of waxed paper.
Make it about 5 inches around and very thin. In the center, put about 2 tablespoons sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon and allspice.
Then place several pieces of margarine on spice.
Dampen the edges of the dough with a little water.
Then fold the dough over to make a little sugar pie.
Roll out the remaining pies.
With a fork, prick holes in the tops of the pies. Line the little pies in the pan but do not put them too close together.
Sprinkle all the pies with a lot of margarine.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour with 1 teaspoon soda.
Cream the sugar and margarine.
Mix eggs and bananas.
Add nuts.
Pour into 1 loaf pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: grandmother's favorite salad
directions: Toss all together and chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: country style chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a heavy 2-quart pan, melt 2/3 cup butter.
Meanwhile, on a piece of waxed paper, combine crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken in butter; roll in crumbs.
Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and chicken is tender.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Add water, oil and vinegar. Stir and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: overnight southwestern egg bake
directions: Generously grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine eggs and half and half; beat slightly.
Stir in corn. Place tortillas in bottom of greased dish.
Pour egg mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Heat oven to 375°.
Cover casserole with foil.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until eggs are just set.
Let stand covered 5 minutes. Uncover; spoon salsa over eggs.
Serve with sour cream and guacamole.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add milk, egg, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch sheet pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo on low heat.
Sift sugar and cocoa.
Add cheese mixture and mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.

title: baked flounder with crab stuffing
directions: Slice across flounder 3 or 4 times on each side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put in a large flat baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Mix crabmeat, dressing mix, onion, bell pepper, egg, water, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Stuff neck of flounder. Put other stuffing in pan around fish.
Cover flounder with bacon strips and raw onion rings.
Onion goes on first.
Bake in a 500° oven for 15 minutes. Then lay a piece of foil loosely over it and set oven at 375° for 20 minutes. Add layer of catsup over fish and cook 5 more minutes.
Cut oven off and leave flounder in oven 10 minutes longer.

title: french banana pancakes
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar into bowl.
Add milk, eggs, butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Heat a lightly greased 6 inch skillet.
Cook batter in large skillet and repeat until all batter is cooked.

title: ping pong
directions: Mix all together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: sangria punch #1
directions: Chill mixture.
At serving time, pour chilled juice over cracked ice.
Top with maraschino cherries, lemon slices or orange slices.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
In same pan, add flour and sugar.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This cake is better when baked in a regular 18 x 12-inch sheet cake pan.

title: party chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in chicken bouillon, onions, celery, etc.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Reserve broth.
Cool.
Heat butter in large saucepan and add flour, 2 tablespoons at a time, blending thoroughly.
Slowly add 4 cups chicken broth from which the fat has been removed.
Add cream, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Combine this mixture with chicken and all other ingredients except noodles.
Boil noodles according to package directions; drain well and stir into chicken mixture.
Taste for seasoning.
Turn into 2 (1 1/2-quart) casseroles or 1 (3-quart) casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and heated thoroughly.
Freezes well.
A 5 to 6 pound hen equals 4 to 5 breasts plus 8 thighs.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar with remaining ingredients.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into a large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: kids punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: fast pace dip
directions: Arrange softened cream cheese on a serving dish.
For added color, place cream cheese on lettuce.
Top cream cheese with Pace picante sauce.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hors d'ouevre dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Make it the day before using.

title: cracker pie
directions: Heat water, cinnamon, margarine, cream of tartar and sugars until margarine melts.

title: strawberry-cranberry mold
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Cool slightly until just beginning to jell, then add rest of the ingredients into a large mold.
Refrigerate.
May serve with mayonnaise and sour cream mixed together.

title: marble loaf cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
Let cool. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sift flour with salt and baking powder; set aside.
In a large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
In medium bowl, combine 1/3 batter with chocolate, mixing well.
Spoon plain and chocolate batters, alternately, into prepared pan.
Cut batter, forming Z.
Bake 65 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on wire rack.
To serve, cut in thin slices.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add rest of ingredients and then add chocolate chips or M&M's.
Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, reserved liquid, strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberries and kiwi slices.
Serves 6 to 8.
If desired, you can use regular graham cracker crust.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple and Jell-O together.
Cool completely, then add buttermilk and Cool Whip and stir.
Add chopped pecans and put in refrigerator until ready.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a baking sheet with cooking spray. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder in a small, shallow bowl.

title: asparagus and cheese casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not put bread cubes into mixture until ready to put in oven.
(One cup of bread cubes = 2 slices.)
This serves about 4 to 6 people.

title: stuffed vidalia onions
directions: *Substitute any large, sweet onions if Vidalias are not available.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Debone chicken.
Mix oleo, onion and celery; cook until brown.
Mix all ingredients; add broth until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot.
In big heavy saucepan, heat butter, onion and garlic cloves.
Stir constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in meat. Warm on low heat.

title: aunt gladys' oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat water, butter and brown sugar together until butter is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Mix dry ingredients.
Pour into wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 4-inch sticks.
Take one stick at a time (refrigerate the rest until needed).
Slice very thin (1/8-inch or less) and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until dark brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350°.
In bowl, beat together until smooth flour, sugar, oil, eggs, salt, orange juice,
vanilla and baking powder.
In a separate bowl, mix apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Put a layer of batter in pan and add a layer of apples, repeating layers three times and ending with apples.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In double boiler melt choc-chips, eagle brand and oleo, add vanilla. Remove from heat. In large bowl, combine marshmallows and nuts, stir in chocolate mixture and drop by tsps. on buttered cookie sheets and chill.

title: grandmother's italian meat pasta sauce
directions: In an 8-quart pot, brown meat and seasoning in oil over medium heat until browned on all sides.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add tomatoes and simmer 4 to 6 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve sauce over your favorite pasta with meat on the side.
This dish can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: main dish pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill for 4 hours or longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pizza style
directions: Beat milk and egg together.
Add to cooked spaghetti.
Place in baking pan.
Cover with sauce, raw hamburger, cheese and pepperoni.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Put cubed bread on bottom of 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Add sausage.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar; whip until fluffy.
Add one egg at a time; whip after each.
Add flour, one cup at a time and beat.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Beat until creamy. Bake in tube pan at 305° for 1 1/2 hours or until the toothpick comes out clean.

title: wassail
directions: Wrap cloves and allspice in a double thickness of cheesecloth. Tie securely.
In an 8-quart pan, heat cider or juice and cranberry juice to boiling point.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into a serving container.
Makes 24 cups.

title: take me to a picnic cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour 15 1/2 X 10 1/2 X 1 inch jelly roll pan.
Combine water, butter, and cocoa in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture boils.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat. Stir together sugar, flour, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Beat until blended.
Add cocoa mixture. Beat until blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Prepare peanut butter chip frosting and spread over cake.
Prepare chocolate garnish and drizzle over top.

title: mariachi drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large plastic bag, combine tortilla chips with taco seasoning mix.
Dampen chicken with water and shake off excess.
Place a few pieces in a plastic
bag; shake thoroughly to coat with chips.
Arrange chicken in a greased, shallow baking pan; bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until chicken is crispy.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; add oil and mix until all traces of oil are gone.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in greased Bundt pan approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients but oats and vanilla. Cook for 2 minutes. Pour over 3 cups quick oats. Stir in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Wash and open the oysters; set aside oysters in shell (discard top shell).
Saute in the butter the garlic cloves and shallots. Add the spinach, bread crumbs, black pepper, Parmesan cheese and Tabasco sauce to frying pan.
Mix together; saute for several minute.
Stuff cooled mixture onto each oyster in the shell.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
One pound browned hamburger works great in place of boiled chicken.

title: heart surgeon's delight
directions: Separate the salami slices in 2 stacks of 5 slices and lay flat on breadboard.
Spread soft cream cheese on four slices and then put them together like a layer cake.
Wrap in cellophane and chill for 1 hour.
Cut the stacked slices like a cake.
Place toothpick in each slice and garnish with slice of black or green olive.
Guaranteed to make a Manhattan taste better!

title: tart cherry jello salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Keep juice and add enough water to make 1 5/8 cup liquid.
Add sugar to juice and bring to a boil.
Stir in jello, until dissolved.
Add fruit and ginger ale.
Stir in nuts and coconut and chill.

title: old fashion lemon pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: lovelight chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar until stiff and glossy; set aside. Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together into large mixer bowl.
Add oil and 1/2 of the milk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed, scraping bowl.
Add remaining milk, oil and egg yolks.

Beat 1 minute and fold in egg whites merinuge. Pour into prepared pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done. If using layer pans (makes 2), grease and flour but line bottom with wax paper and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: catfish jambalaya
directions: Put chopped onions, chopped garlic, chopped celery, margarine, Ro-Tel tomatoes and sliced mushrooms in saucepan.
Cook until mixture starts to turn light brown.
Season with salt and red pepper to taste while mixture is cooking.
Add catfish and cook 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Mix with cooked rice.
Top with green onions.
Serve hot.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Mix together in large bowl with other ingredients. Spoon into well-greased muffin tins and bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and then fold in Tater Tots. Sprinkle with 1 cup bread crumbs and drizzle with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt. Cut Crisco into flour mixture with pastry blender. Add enough milk to make a soft dough. There will be enough dough for 2 double-crust pies. Pat half of the dough into 2 pie pans. Save other half for top crust or biscuits.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cookie sheet in oven to preheat. In large bowl, combine corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Place chocolate chips and pecans in bottom of pie crust.
