Pour syrup mixture over pecans.
Place pie on heated cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until deep golden brown and filling is set.
Cool completely.
Store in refrigerator.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Microwave chips in large bowl for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave 1 minute more.
Add peanut butter and blend well.
Pour in corn flakes and stir to coat thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool until hard.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add mashed cranberry sauce. Stir until smooth.
Add cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Combine lemon cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in 10x sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place halved strawberries in baked pie shells.
Cook other ingredients in saucepan until mixture turns dark red and thickens on medium heat.
Pour over strawberries and chill 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: summer shrimp salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix ingredients together in a large bowl. Chill before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie(diabetic)
directions: Mix together and pour in crust. Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese spread
directions: In large bowl, beat soup, cheese, onion and taco sauce until smooth.
Can be shaped into log or ball shape and rolled in chopped nuts or chives.
But is very good plain, spread on crackers.

title: clara's pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco together.
Add mixture of vinegar, egg and water.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions to 1/4-inch thickness.
Separate into rings. Beat remaining ingredients together.
Dip onion rings in batter. Deep fat fry until golden brown.

title: oven grilled cheddar steak
directions: Put the 3 tablespoons of steak sauce on the steak.
Then put 1/4 cup chopped pecans on the meat.
Put 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Bake the steak at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let it cool for 1 minute before eating.

title: corn fritters
directions: Fry as pancakes and serve with butter or syrup.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt, mixing well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and Amaretto.
Fold in sliced peaches.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
If desired, drizzle cake with powdered sugar glaze on top of each slice with a peach slice dipped in lemon juice.

title: apple butter spice cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of a 13 x 9 inch cake pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixing bowl.
Cream at high speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Blend in apple butter and vanilla extract.
At low speed add sifted ingredients alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Sprinkle half of mixture over batter. Spoon remaining batter into pan, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle the rest of the brown sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until cake springs back when lightly touched in the center.

title: mexican date roll
directions: Place sugar, salt, milk and Karo in deep pan.
Heat and stir until it boils.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and dates.
Cool.
Beat until creamy. Add nuts. Pour into pan and cut in squares.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Defrost spinach.
Drain and squeeze out water.
Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas.
Roll tortillas and cut into 3/4-inch slices. Chill until ready to serve.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburg and season with salt and pepper; drain and place in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cover hamburg with corn.
Be sure hamburg is covered.
Cover corn with potatoes.
Dot potatoes with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until potatoes brown a little on top.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil and add onions,
salt and bacon until bacon is soft, but not colored.
Add
tomatoes
and
the other ingredients. Partially cover pan
and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Sauce should be fairly thick.

title: no egg oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flavoring.
Blend in flour and soda.
Stir in oatmeal.
Using hands, form the dough in a circle about the size of a quarter.
Put on cookie sheet (greased lightly).
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: swedish pastry
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add slightly beaten egg yolk and then add flour.
Mix until dough is formed.
Roll in medium size balls.
Dip them in egg white and roll in crushed walnuts or pecans.
Press down centers with finger.
Bake for 5 minutes in a 325° oven.
Remove from oven and press down again.
Replace in oven and bake from 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, fill with jam.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix by directions on box.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per instructions on box.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch pans.
When cake is cool, place one layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding per instructions on box.
Place 1/2 mixed pudding on top of cake, followed with 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 fruit cocktail and 1/2 cherries.
Place one container Cool Whip on top. Continue with next cake layer and proceed as before.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and nuts.

title: dressing
directions: Pour this over cauliflower, onion (sliced in rings), bacon bits, and bits of lettuce.

title: holiday apple and cranberry casserole
directions: Put the apples, cranberries and sugar in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Mix the oats, brown sugar and pecans and pour over the top of fruits.
Dot the entire top with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: berner sauce
directions: Bring wine, vinegar and spices to a boil.
Strain.
When cool, stir in egg yolks and half the butter.
Place in double boiler over hot but not boiling water and gradually add remaining butter, beating constantly until thick.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Dice artichoke hearts into tiny pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top should be brown.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Toss apples and bananas with lemon juice just to coat.
Mix all fruit together.
Add Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Mix well. Top with sliced almonds.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put in container with lid 3/4 cup sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir.
Cut biscuit into quarters; put in container and shake until all pieces are covered with sugar and cinnamon.
In saucepan, put 1 cup brown sugar, 1 1/2 sticks butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cook on high; bring to boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Spray Bundt pan with oil; put biscuits in pan and cover with glaze.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and turn over on plate.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruits; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate.
Beat well with rotary beater until blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Mix in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: To squash, add cornstarch.
Mix salt, pepper, onion, cheese, milk and dressing.
Mix and then stir in margarine and eggs.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: "special" baked beans
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, add sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze water from spinach.
Add other ingredients and chill overnight.
Cut out the middle of Hawaiian bread loaf so that the loaf becomes an edible bowl for the dip.
Cut middle insert of bread into chunks.
Put spinach mixture inside of bread and serve, using the bread chunks for dipping.

title: hamburger one-dish meal
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine in heavy skillet. Add hamburger, broken into pieces.
Cook until tender and brown. Combine corn and eggs.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Prepare shrimp.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Stir in cream slowly.
When sauce is thick, stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce and shrimp.
Stir until well heated.
Season with salt, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Add sherry right before serving.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Whip the egg white and water until frothy, not stiff.
Mix together sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over nuts. Fold into egg white and water.
Spread in a single layer onto cookie sheet. Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cook 3 1/2 hours.
Stir every 1/2 to 1 hour while cooking.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: dijon chicken breast
directions: Cut chicken into serving size pieces; pound thin.
Beat eggs, water, green onions and mustard in medium bowl.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Dip in egg mixture, coating well.
Coat with bread crumbs, pressing crumbs into chicken.
Melt margarine in skillet, add oil and heat.
Saute chicken for 5 minutes on each side or until done.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour 1/2 batter into greased casserole dish.
top with chilies and cheese, then pour other 1/2 of batter over that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and ham quiche
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add soup and half and half, blending well.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and broccoli in pie crust and pour egg mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is firm.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Try other soup, cheese, meat and vegetable mixtures for variety.
Serves 6.

title: bread pot fondue
directions: Slice off top of bread.
Reserve top.
Hollow the inside leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into cubes.
Combine cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in ham, onion, chilies and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into hollowed loaf.
Replace top.
Wrap loaf in several layers of aluminum foil.
Set on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Meanwhile, toast the bread cubes with the melted butter and oil. When the filled loaf is done, stir, then serve with the toasted bread cubes.

title: molasses spice balls
directions: Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook onions in boiling salted water until tender and then drain.
In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine; blend in flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Place broccoli and onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over.
Mix lightly.
Top with cheese.
Melt remaining butter and toss with crumbs and set aside.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Cream the butter and honey.
Mix in flour and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in oven at 325° for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
In small bowl, combine cinnamon and sugar.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Cool upright in pan 25 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix butter and crackers.
Put on top of other mixed vegetables.

title: orange swizzle
directions: Reconstitute orange juice with ginger ale.
Pour over crushed ice.
Serve with orange slices and cherry.
Makes 6 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a hot well-greased 8X8-inch pan.
Bake at 450° about 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: buttery cornbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine eggs and milk.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan and bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured well, in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour or more, until cake springs back when pressed lightly with finger.

title: grandma's butter cream frosting
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar and cream again. Then add milk slowly. Add salt and vanilla and beat at high speed for 5 minutes or more. This frosting can be stored up to 6 weeks in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: gooey bars
directions: Beat butter, 1 egg and cake mix into a ball, then spread evenly in a rectangular shaped pan.
In a separate bowl, beat the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour on top of dough.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cool.

title: vegetable lime ring(salad)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until partially set, then combine remaining ingredients and fold into partially set jello.
Transfer mixture to 3 1/2 cup ring.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, butter, vinegar and water in pan.
Boil gently without stirring until it forms a "hard click" ball when tested in cold water.
Add soda and mix well.
Pour over the popped corn, mixing as fast as possible, so each kernel is covered with the mixture.
When cool, butter your hands and form size of balls you desire.
This will keep the corn mixture from burning your hands.

title: chocolate cappuccino
directions: Stir Espresso, sugar and salt in 4 cup measure. Add chocolate. Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is melted and can be stirred in smooth.
Stir in milk.
Microwave, uncovered 2 to 3 minutes or until hot.
Beat with hand mixer until foamy. Top each serving with whipped cream. Sprinkle with orange peel. Yields 4 servings.
Contains 140 calories per serving.

title: crunchy pecan topping
directions: Mix pecans and brown sugar in small bowl.
Drizzle with butter. Stir until mixture is uniformly moistened.
Sprinkle over cooled pumpkin pie.
Broil about 5 to 8 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve while warm or let cool.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: eggnog macaroon cream(with raspberry sauce)
directions: Soften gelatin in 1 C. eggnog; stir over low heat until dissolved.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Blend in remaining eggnog, sour cream and extract.
Chill until thickened but not set.
Fold whipping cream and cookies into eggnog mixture.
Pour into mold (2 qt. size) and chill till firm.
Unmold and serve with raspberry sauce.

title: squash casserole(side dish)
directions: Boil or steam (I steam) squash and onion with pepper until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain well, then let sit and drain again.
Mix soup and sour cream together in a large bowl.
Then fold in squash and onion.
Set aside.
Melt butter and toss in stuffing.
Put layer of buttered stuffing mix (1/2 of stuffing mixture) on bottom of a 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Add squash mixture and sprinkle the rest of the stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 9 servings.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon in confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for approximately 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Makes around 100 cookies.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Slice the zucchini with the skin real thin or grate it. Throw all ingredients in large
bowl
and
mix
well.
Put
in greased pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until brown.
Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: macadamia nut and white chocolate cookies
directions: Cover 2 baking sheets with parchment or aluminum foil; set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt into a medium bowl; set aside.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: fingers liver spread
directions: Boil livers. Fry onions in fat until lightly browned. Blend livers, eggs and onions (or put through meat grinder; fine grind). Add fat to make right spreading consistency. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer on low speed about 1 1/2 minutes until well blended. Add zucchini and melted, cooled chocolate; stir to blend.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts to egg mixture. Stir just enough to blend in dry ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased and parchment lined or greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool on rack.

title: one-bowl carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl with a sturdy whisk, beat the eggs with the sugar until thick.
Slowly add the oil in a steady stream, mixing constantly.
Mix in the vanilla.
Measure the flour in a 2-cup measuring cup and mix in the salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
With a mixing whisk, mix into the liquid ingredients until smooth. Stir in the carrots and walnuts until thoroughly combined.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch layer or square pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until a tester inserted in center comes out with a crumb clinging to it.
Cool pan on rack 10 minutes; then remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: shrimp clam sauce with linguini
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions and garlic and cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour and mustard.
Add liquid from clams, water, wine, parsley, basil, and salt.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams and shrimp; heat to serving temperature.
Serve over linguini.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix pineapple and dates.
Spread this mixture between vanilla wafers.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Roll in coconut; chill before serving.

title: enchilada pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add enchilada sauce, onions and olives. In cake pan, layer: tortillas, meat, sauce and cheese.
Top with tortilla; pour 1/2 can tomato sauce over each pie and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Put sour cream on serving.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer ingredients in the following manner:
Put rice in the bottom with corn on top of the rice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 1 can of tomato sauce, 1 can water, onion and ground beef.
Top with second can of tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Cover top layer with bacon strips.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef pieces in small amount of oil.
When meat is brown, season with salt, pepper and onion salt.
Add soup and water; simmer gently for 40 to 50 minutes or until meat is tender.
Fold in mushrooms and sour cream; bring to serving temperatures.
If thinner gravy is desired, thin with dry, light red wine.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft (then mash).
Add milk and butter until potatoes are creamy, but firm.
Brown the ground beef.
Add onion, mushrooms, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel (optional).
Ro-Tel will make it a little more spicier.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove chicken and bone and cut up when cooled.
Skim broth and add bouillon cubes.
Add cut up chicken, can of creamed corn, noodles and seasonings.
Add more water as needed.

title: broiled hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) and marinate chicken in them for 2 to 3 hours before broiling. Baste during cooking. Cook until chicken is tender.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cook
all ingredients except sweet potatoes until thickened. Pour
over
sweet
potatoes and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, oleo and soup in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese, almonds and paprika on top. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and bacon.
Place half the mixture in loaf pan; indent in center.
Place cheese in center.
Seal with remaining mixture; top with slices of bacon. Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix together, then form a ball. Pour seafood cocktail sauce on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil
chicken until tender. Bone and cut up into pieces. Saute veggies in butter until tender and light brown.
Add soup and broth, grated cheese, chicken, tomatoes, Tabasco and salt. Cook spaghetti.
Drain. Add to above. Add olives.
Cover and bake at 350°for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly combine mashed fruit and yogurt in a bowl.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well.
Spoon mixture into crust; freeze for about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in water until thick.
Add cheese and butter to hot grits.
Place eggs in 1-cup measure; add milk to make 1 cup.
Beat and add to grits.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat egg until light and add to creamed mixture.
In a separate bowl, sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add dry mixture to batter alternately with milk.
Add diced apple.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Butter the bottom of a 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Cut rhubarb to cover bottom of pan.
Spread sugar over rhubarb.
Spread jello over rhubarb.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Put over rhubarb mix and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and serve as upside down cake.

title: jen's breakfast casserole
directions: Make this casserole the night before you serve it and place in refrigerator.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased casserole pan with cheese on top.
In the morning, place in oven and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: christmas salad(good anytime of the year.)
directions: Put gelatin and marshmallows into a mixing bowl. Add boiling water and stir until marshmallows are partially melted.
Add pineapple, then mix and place in refrigerator until slightly jelled.
Remove from refrigerator and add nuts (if desired), cottage cheese and cherries.
Mix together well and fold in whipping cream that has been beaten stiff. Return to refrigerator to jell. Serve on lettuce leaves or serve alone.

title: southern spiced pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin.
Then mix in milk.
Pour into pie shell and bake in 400° oven for approximately 50 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix with popcorn quickly before it hardens and spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: yellow squash cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Bake in a floured
and greased tube pan for 55 minutes at 350°.
Different but delicious.

title: honey butter
directions: Take along a small bottle of vinegar and an aluminum pie plate.
Set about 20 feet away from the picnic table.
This will keep away those pesky, little, black, hard-shelled bugs.

title: ritzy squash casserole
directions: Place squash in a saucepan with a small amount of water; cook until tender. Drain and mash. Add other ingredients to squash. Butter a casserole dish and spoon in mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done it has consistency of pudding. Serves 6.

title: no sugar banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Stir in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer in a large bowl or long flat Pyrex dish, starting with vanilla wafers, then bananas, then pudding. This make a large amount.
You will have two layers of each.
I sprinkle some lemon juice on banana slices to keep from turning dark.
I chill before serving.
I sometimes use 1 package of vanilla and 1 package of banana pudding mix.

title: loaded mashed potato casserole
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese and bacon, in a large bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium-high speed until potatoes are fairly smooth and creamy.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13x9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
If you prefer extra crispy bacon, reserve bacon and sprinkle at the end of cooking.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add bread cubes and sugar; cook slowly. Stir in tomatoes and seasoning.
Place mixture in buttered shallow pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sausage, cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Put on greased biscuit pan and bake at 350° until brown.
Drop by tablespoon onto pan.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg thoroughly.
Shape firmly into 6 patties (1/2-inch thick).
In medium skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Cook patties until browned.
Set patties aside; pour off fat.
Add remaining soup and water.
Heat to boil.
Return patties to pan.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes, or until patties are no longer pink (160°).
Serves 6.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Sauce:
Melt chocolate squares with condensed milk and cook until very thick.
Add hot water, salt and sugar and cook until mixture is very smooth and of desired thickness.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil on both sides, salt and pepper to taste.

title: pralines
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Add pecan halves.
Cook to boil and boil for 3 to 5 minutes or until reasonably soft. Remove from heat.

title: president's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to a broil.
In a large skillet, combine margarine, lemon juice, salt and spices.
Cook over low heat until margarine has melted.

title: creme de menthe bars(3 layer cookies)
directions: Melt chocolate in oil.
Mix with brown sugar, eggs, flour, salt and soda.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: carrots almondine
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Turn into well-greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until carrots are glazed.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Tear tortilla shells in pieces.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer the tortillas, chicken, soups and cheese.
Repeat until all are used.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon nut mixture(magic reindeer feet)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large saucepan, cover almonds and pecans with water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 1 minute.
Drain well.

title: luscious cherry bars
directions: Mix flour,
butter
and confectioners sugar; press in a 13 x 9-inch
greased
pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Mix brown
sugar
and eggs until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; stir in remaining
ingredients.
Bake
for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Frost when cool.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Dough will be stiff.
Divide dough into half.
Make each half into a long roll or square roll.
Wrap in wax paper and put in icebox for several hours.
Slice and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 300° only until lightly brown.
Watch carefully.
Sprinkle, while hot, with powdered sugar.
Store in tight fitting tin.
(Takes about 12 minutes.)

title: gooey cake
directions: Combine cake mix and butter with two of the eggs.
Beat one minute.
Spread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add other two eggs and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add all but 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix in the pan and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, cool 30 minutes and sprinkle with remaining powdered sugar.

title: quick and easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish (amount depends on quantity of chicken).
Finely crush saltines.
Roll chicken in melted margarine, then roll in saltines.
Melt a little more margarine in dish.
Place chicken in dish and bake approximately 20 minutes. Turn chicken and bake another 20 minutes.

title: spooky spiders
directions: Stir together, except noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Stick noodles in sides for legs.
Add small colored candies for eyes.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cream puff bars
directions: Boil for 7 minutes until side leaves kettle.
Spread in ungreased pan or cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Beat cream cheese, milk and pudding together.
Put on top of crust. Put in fridge.
Chill and cover with Dream Whip.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and cream thoroughly until fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add 4 eggs, 2 at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition, on medium speed. Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving. Top with whipped cream and nuts, if desired.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together the cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the cherry Jell-O on top.
Add the crushed pineapple and the chopped nuts.
Mix together and chill.

title: eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix over crackers.
Cover with another layer of crackers.
Add remaining pudding mix and cover with another layer of crackers.

title: pooh bear sammich("just for kids")
directions: Toast the bread.
Spread honey and peanut butter on slices and fold them together.
Cook in a microwave on full power for 30 seconds.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add margarine. Add warm water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/3 cup flour.
Beat again 2 minutes at high speed.
Add rest of flour to make a soft dough.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease each side.
Cover tightly .
Refrigerate 2 hours or up to 2 days. Punch down and form rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 30 minutes depending on size of rolls.

title: quiche
directions: Crumble bacon and put in pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour in crust.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jew bread
directions: Cook eggs and sugar in double boiler for 10 minutes.
Cool and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and top with whipped cream.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Marinate meat in vinegar, bay leaves and sliced onion for 3 days, using enough vinegar to cover.
Pat dry; coat with flour and sear (in Dutch oven) in shortening.
Add vinegar and onion marinade after removing rye bread and bay leaves.
Lower heat; cover.
Let cook about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Thicken gravy if desired.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: sherbet salad
directions: Put all ingredients together in bowl to mix.
Either pour in mold or into favorite glass serving dish.

title: easy chicken and mushroom casserole
directions: Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Cover chicken with soup.
Cover dish and bake at 350° until chicken is done.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to a low boil.
Add cream cheese and gelatin.
Stir until smooth over heat.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise, vegetables and shrimp.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serve with crackers for an appetizer.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Stir in bread, meat and cheese.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, making sure it is completely dissolved.
Stir in pineapple with juice, pie filling and nuts.
Mix well. Pour into dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: guilt-free roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut into 4 lengthwise quarters.

title: uncle wesley's creamed eggs
directions: Peel hard-boiled eggs and chop up; set aside.
Melt butter. Add flour and stir together well.
Add milk slowly over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens (approximately 5 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add chopped eggs, garlic, salt and pepper.
Serve hot over toast for an excellent breakfast!

title: dilly bread
directions: In warm mixing bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
In small saucepan heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Add to dissolved yeast. Add egg, sugar, onion, butter and dill seed.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to other ingredients; stir until blended.
Dough will be quite soft.
Let dough rise for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal potato chips
directions: Slice potatoes crosswise into paper-thin rounds; brush with safflower oil.
Bake on a Teflon baking sheet at 425° for 20 minutes.
Turn; bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown and crisp.

title: black velvet cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in small mixing bowl until blended.
Add cocoa, alternately with milk, beating smooth. Gradually add and fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into pie crust; chill until firm or freeze.
Thaw at least 15 minutes before serving if frozen.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quickie pluck 'n' cake
directions: Open biscuits; quarter each.
Place in brown bag.
Mix cinnamon with 1 cup sugar; pour over biscuits and shake well to coat each piece.
Place pieces on a Bundt pan.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; turn onto plate.
Can pluck pieces from cake.

title: pasta with red clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet saute garlic in hot oil over medium heat about 30 seconds.
Add black and red pepper.
Cook and stir for 30 seconds or more.
Drain clams, save juice; set clams aside.
Add reserved clam juice and undrained tomatoes to skillet.
Stir in parsley, basil and anchovy paste.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat. Simmer uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes or to desired consistency. Stir in clams, heat through.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well.
Serve sauce over cooked pasta.

title: creamy corn and zucchini
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in oleo until zucchini is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients and heat through.

title: italian soup
directions: Fill large soup pot with about 3 quarts water.
Add paste, bouillon, spinach and spices.
Simmer at least one hour.
Add the lortellini one half hour before serving.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
This is hearty enough for a meal.
Serve warm with Italian bread.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion, celery, pimentos and green pepper in 1 stick margarine.
Mix the soups in the veggies.
Add the chopped chicken and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Chill dough.
Roll in walnut size balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: mommom's sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll on lightly floured board.
Cut and decorate with nuts or raisins, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough into a 17 x 11 1/2 x1 inch pan.
Bake until golden brown and cool.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing until creamy.
Spread over cooled crescent rolls and sprinkle with chopped vegetables.
Pat into creamed cheese and cut into squares.
Prepare ahead and refrigerate.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion over medium heat; drain.
Add cubed Velveeta and melt.
Add entire can Ro-tel.
Reduce heat to low. Must keep warm while serving.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar and water until if forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour hot mixture over stiffly beaten egg white, beating constantly.
Add nuts and vanilla, beating until stiff.
When nearly set, drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Will harden when cool.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat or cook stew beef in small amount of water until tender.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn and cook until beans are about done.
Then add okra and cook until tender.
Makes extra to freeze.

title: rose petal yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; stir in sugar. Beat in remaining ingredients, blending well. Fill greased muffin tins about 1/2 full of batter and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: beef kabobs(4 to 6 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, combine steak sauce, water, brown sugar, mustard and lemon juice.
Blend well.
Add beef cubes and toss coat. Marinate for at least 1 hour (but no longer than 24 hours) in refrigerator. Bring 1-quart of water to a boil. Boil onions for 10 minutes.

title: sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt first four ingredients in saucepan.
Pour mixture over remaining ingredients.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (do not overbake).

title: a good chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Last, add boiling water with soda.
Bake at 350° until springs back when touched in center.

title: mrs. annie crosby's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and cook together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Freeze.

title: broiled teriyaki chops
directions: Combine all except chops.
Marinate chops in mixture in refrigerator, 1 to 2 hours.
Remove; keep marinade.
Place chops on broiler rack.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush with marinade.
Turn once.
You'll know they're perfectly cooked when a meat thermometer inserted registers 160°.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, but not brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, lemon peel and parsley.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles.
Blend in sour cream.
Add beans. Heat through, stirring.

title: quick and easy cinnamon buns
directions: Brown buns in either oven or toaster oven.
Butter, sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon sugar.

title: shrimp dip or spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.

title: new alsace church picnic dressing
directions: Dip slices of bread into a bowl of water.
Soak and squeeze out water. Do not squeeze out too dry. Lightly separate bread and place in bowl.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir in Jell-O.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Pour into mold or Pyrex dish and refrigerate until firm, light and delicious.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and continue beating. Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add walnuts to the sifted flour mixture.
Add nuts and dry ingredients to the oil mixture, then fold in grated carrots.
Pour cake mix into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Refrigerate cake after frosting.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain off most of the juice.
Add pudding (dry).
Mix well in fruit.
When ready to serve, add some bananas.
Chill before serving.

title: taco twists
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until the meat is no longer pink. Drain. Add the cheese, salsa, chilies, garlic powder, hot pepper sauce, salt and cumin. Mix well. Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 12 rectangles. Place on ungreased baking sheets. Press perforations to seal. Place 1/2 cup meat mixture in the center of each rectangle. Bring 4 corners to the center and twist. Pinch to seal. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 12 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together the hamburger, onion and stuffing mix.
Roll into balls and fry.
Combine barbecue sauce, water, brown sugar and sweet pickle relish.
Place meatballs in crock-pot and pour mixture over meatballs.
Simmer in crock-pot.

title: pasta with parsley, garlic and basil sauce
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well; place in a large bowl.
Set aside and keep warm. Saute garlic in olive oil until lightly browned.
Pour over hot pasta.
Add Parmesan cheese and remaining ingredients, tossing until pasta is coated and butter is melted.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cherry trifle
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to directions.
Add sour cream and chill.
Cut slices of angel food cake and make a layer in the bottom of the trifle dish (layer about 1 1/2 inches deep). Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sherry or brandy.
Add 1 can pie filling and spread evenly.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Spread evenly. Repeat layers and chill at least 24 hours for flavors to mix. Just before serving, top with Cool Whip or real whipped cream. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Add flavoring.
Turn burner off and quickly add other ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper and let set until cookies harden.
Makes 24 to 30 cookies, depending on spoon-size chosen.

title: key west guava bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Soak in water 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour into a colander; drain.
Squeeze most of water out.
Place bread in large bowl, add eggs, milks, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add to mixture, then combine well and add back to pan.
Cut guava paste into crosswise strips.
Lay atop mixture in rows, almost touching.
Push guava paste below liquid level, then bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour.
Check center for doneness.
It will fall, that's okay.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hot wings
directions: Coat chicken in flour and fry until golden brown.
Mix together Tabasco sauce, Italian dressing and margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Dip wings in sauce to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and broil for 10 minutes.

title: tommie's egg custard
directions: After scalding milk and sugar, add 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour mixture into deep pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: western new york barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Baste on chicken or pork chops while grilling.
Keep unused sauce in refrigerator.

title: spinach salad with honey dressing
directions: Sprinkle salt in salad bowl.
Rub garlic into salt using the back of a wooden spoon.
Add honey, oil and lemon juice.
Beat with a wire whisk; refrigerate.
Chill.
Add spinach, oranges and walnuts to dressing.
Toss gently.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherry juice into saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch, butter, salt, almond extract and coloring.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cherries.
Pour into unbaked bottom crust and top with lattice top crust.
Bake 10 minutes in a preheated 425° oven, then at 375°, bake for 25 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat 7-Up or Sprite just to boiling and dissolve jello in it. Cool slightly.
Add sour cream using a wire whisk until smooth. Add pineapple with juice.
Pour into a mold or rectangular dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: deluxe potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine and cornflakes in a casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top of casserole and pour melted margarine over top.
Place in oven again and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and cool whip, add pineapple.
Place in pie shells and chill.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in sauce pan over low heat.
Do not overheat.
In a mixing bowl blend flour, salt, sugar, slightly beaten eggs and vanilla. Add melted butter and chocolate. Blend together.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° until firm to the touch. Watch carefully and do not over cook.
Cut into pie wedges and serve with a scoop of ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except save half the cheese. Put the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: oven-fried chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound each half breast between plastic wrap until it is thin enough to roll.
Use ready to eat ham.
Trim off fat.
On each half chicken breast, place a slice of ham and a slice of cheese. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley.
Roll up and rotate first in mayonnaise, then in crumbs.
Should be lightly coated.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 casseroles (1 1/2-quart size).

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Mix 2 bouillon cubes in hot water and set aside until mixed well.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter after chopping up.
In a medium casserole dish, mix all ingredients and stir well.
Salt to taste.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, then mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the tomatoes, onions, chilies and black olives.
Refrigerate and serve with Doritos.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around 10-12 beans. Secure with toothpick. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over bundles. Bake covered at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Bake an additional 15 minutes uncovered.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Put in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
Shake 2 or 3 squares in confectioners sugar in a bag until all squares are completely coated.

title: dorothy's berry peek-a-boos
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugars.
Add eggs, water and extract; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients and oats.
Drop dough by the teaspoon onto a sprayed cookie sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon jam on each cookie, pressing gently into dough.
Top with another level teaspoon of dough.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave quick tomato soup
directions: Pour juice into microwavable cup or bowl.
Season with lemon pepper, salt and Creole seasoning to taste.
Heat about 2 minutes. Serves 1.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together until fluffy.
Mix in the zucchini, nuts and vanilla.
Sift the flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together and stir into egg mixture.
Bake in two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in small strips.
Sprinkle with tenderizer and let stand 10 minutes.
Place in foil.
Sprinkle with salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Sprinkle dry gravy mix over steak.
Add onion and green pepper.
Dot with butter.
Wrap with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes in hot oven at 425°.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 1 hour longer.

title: creamy corn
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add chicken breast to salad dressing and blend gradually.
Mix the chicken, celery, pecans, olives, salt and pepper.
Add salad dressing and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Cook over medium heat the corn syrup and sugar until comes to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until blended. Remove from heat.
Pour over cereal; mix well.
Spread evenly in a greased pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes 24 squares.

title: peanutty cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons of sugar and melted butter in small bowl; press 1 level tablespoonful of crumb mixture into bottom of each of 12 paper-lined 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.

title: orange bread custard
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, egg, salt, vanilla and orange peel. Gradually add scalded milk, stirring constantly. Add bread cubes and raisins; mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart buttered baking dish.
Place dish in a pan of warm water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a silver knife comes out clean when inserted in center.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute in heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats; mix quickly.
Beat until thick.
Drop onto wax paper with tablespoon.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until glazed.
Serves 4.

title: hot buttered cider
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in spices.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve (keeps indefinitely).

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix water and powdered milk.
Add sugar, oil, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add yeast mixture, then add flour.
Let rise, then roll out.

title: simple simon cookies
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature and blend with pudding mix.
Add flour and mix well.
Roll into little balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pineapple mint supreme
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Cut oleo into mixture. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in vanilla and orange peel.
Add zucchini, alternately stir in dry and milk mixture, including nuts in the last addition.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Combine carrots, bell pepper, onion, celery in bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over salad, tossing to coat.
Marinate covered overnight.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep for up to 3 weeks.

title: bread pudding
directions: Trim crusts and cube bread.
Soak bread in milk.
Beat eggs and add to bread mixture.
Add sugar and vanilla and blend well. Pour into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for about 45 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: grilled potato fans
directions: With a sharp knife, make cuts 1/2 inch apart in each potato, leaving slices attached at the bottom.
Fan the potatoes slightly. Place each on a piece of heavy-duty foil (about 12-inch sq.). Insert onions and butter between potato slices.
Sprinkle with celery, salt, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Fold foil around potatoes and seal tightly.
Grill, covered, over medium-hot heat for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except preserves. Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Spray muffin tins with Pam and fill each halfway with mixture.
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves in center and cover with more batter.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Add olive oil and garlic.
Saute garlic for about a minute.
Remove from heat.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Spread evenly in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine cheese, sugar, onion, oleo, dill seed and salt in saucepan.
Heat, but do not boil.
Let cool. Add dissolved yeast and egg. Combine flour and soda.
Add liquids to flour and stir.

Let set until dough has doubled in size. Turn dough out on floured board and knead for 1 minute. Divide into 2 loaves and let double in size again. Bake at 350°. Butter tops of loaves and sprinkle with seasoned salt.

title: old-fashioned apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle on apples.
Combine sugar, flour, egg, salt and baking powder.
Spread over apple slices. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gorgeous turkey
directions: Sieve flour and salt; set aside.
In a pan, heat margarine in water to gently melt the margarine, then bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add flour and vigorously mix with a wooden spoon until the thick paste leaves sides of pan clean.
Beat eggs into paste with electric mixer.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add in dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oil and water in slowly, keeping mixture smooth. Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease with butter and flour a loaf pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Cool; cut into slices.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil together 15 to 20 minutes the cranberries, sugar, water and salt.
Add jello and marshmallows.
Stir occasionally. When partly congealed, add celery, apples and nuts.

title: bavarian squares
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Cream oleo and sugar; add egg yolks, flour, vanilla and egg whites.
Pour onto a cookie sheet, reserving about 1/4 of the dough.
Pour pie filling over and drop remaining dough.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and squeeze out juice.
Melt butter and add onion over low heat for 10 minutes, then cool.
Add remaining ingredients to the onion, butter and spinach.
Chill mixture. Shape into balls and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jewish onion pletzyls(flats)
directions: In a large bowl sprayed with Pam mix flour, sugar and salt. Add eggs, oil, warm water and yeast mixture.
Mix and form into a ball, dough will be loose.
Cover ball with oil, cover bowl with towel and put into a prewarmed oven (180° and then shut off) to rise until double (about 2 hours).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and almonds.
Put in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish; let stand overnight.
Take from refrigerator about 3 hours before baking to bring to room temperature.
Garnish with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbling.
Makes about 10 servings.
Or use chicken breasts for 8 people.

title: homemade face paint i(child-approved)
directions: Face painting done in creative shapes and designs is a nice alternative to wearing a mask on Halloween night (masks can be very frightening to preschoolers and they obscure vision when a child is walking up and down steps or when crossing the street).
In addition to using face paint to complete a Halloween costume, kids will enjoy this recipe for birthday parties, staging a backyard play and for dress-up on a rainy day.

title: nellie's sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients together in bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Remove from heat.
Cook; pour over kraut mixture and let stand for 24 hours.

title: cheese rolls or balls
directions: Let cheese set at room temperature.
Work together when soft. Add salt, pecans and garlic.
Mix well.
Roll in 5 rolls or 2 balls.
Roll in chili powder, parsley leaves or paprika.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
Slice and serve on crackers.
Will freeze good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place pieces of chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Bring to a boil the cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix the stuffing and corn bread together and pour hot chicken broth that the chicken was cooked in, over this.
Mix well.
Make dressing a medium thickness.
Put on top of chicken and bake in a 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Make pie crust.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Add lemon juice and rind.
Mix sugar, flour and salt, then add to lemon mixture.
Stir in melted butter and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie crust.
Put into 425° oven for first 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Melt shortening in heavy saucepan.
Brown meat over medium heat.
Add 1 can tomato soup and 2 soup cans water.
Cover and let cook slowly until tender, about 1 hour.
Add 3 carrots, sliced, 3 potatoes, cut in 4 pieces and 2 onions cut into 4 pieces. Cover and continue cooking slowly until tender.
If there is not enough liquid, add more water during cooking.
If stew is too thin, remove lid and cook until thickened.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto sheet (cookie will spread).
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: low calorie chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Soften margarine; add cheese, salt, pepper, Rice Krispies and flour.
Mix well.
Form into small balls and flatten with fork. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Drain oranges and crushed pineapple.
Chop orange slices. Combine nondairy topping, cottage cheese and jello in a large bowl.
Fold in well-drained orange slices, pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and vegetarian soup.
Let simmer about 10 minutes.
Put all this mixture in a casserole bowl.
Top this mixture with whipped potatoes, then add cheese.
Cook in oven 25 minutes at 325°.
Good to the last drop.

title: french kraut
directions: Mix and heat to a boil:
vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt, mustard and turmeric.
After mixture comes to a boil, add 1 cup Wesson oil.
Mix together with vegetables and chill.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat, pickling spices, salt and vinegar in large pan or bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 to 6 days.
Turn meat daily. Transfer meat into roasting pan.
Cover and cook at low heat (325°) until nearly tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour add onions.
Thicken juice with flour to desired consistency using some of the marinade.
Meat may be sliced and placed with gravy in roasting pan and reheated when desired.
It will not crumble like ordinary pot roast.
Serve with red cabbage, or sauerkraut and potato pancakes for a German meal.	Serves 6.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Can be frozen in 1/2 gallon jugs for future use.
Absolutely excellent for showers, weddings or any occasion.
Looks beautiful in a punch bowl. Freeze a bowl full for the punch bowl for an extra touch.

title: mom's grape pie
directions: Wash fruit. Separate skin from pulp. Save skins; cook pulp. Put cooked pulp through Foley mill to remove seeds. Combine skins, pulp, and other ingredients. Bake in a 9-inch double crust at 400° for approx. 1 hour.

title: no crust fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs together.
Melt butter and cocoa together and add to first mixture.
Add pecans that have been chopped.
Bake in buttered 8-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sausage - sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch thick slices; arrange half the sausage in bottom of greased casserole.
Peel and core apples; cut into crosswise slices.
Arrange half the apples over sausage.
Add caraway seed to sauerkraut; spread over apple mixture.
Arrange remaining sausage slices on sauerkraut; top with remaining apple slices.
Pour bacon fat over top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Place in a gallon jug the first 3 ingredients.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour in the jug.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
This will keep in refrigerator or you can freeze in containers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 1 hour.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup crackers; sprinkle reserved crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 2 (1 quart) casseroles or 1 large casserole.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. No longer than 15 minutes (just brown).
Cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add just enough of the milk to make a paste.
Add egg yolks, heat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in remaining milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, stirring until melted.
Pour into pie shell.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with electric mixer at high speed until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar and vanilla, beating until stiff peaks form. Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 350° about 5 minutes, until meringue is lightly browned.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine ingredients and steam 3 hours.

title: potatoes and cabbage
directions: Fry sausage until done.
Add chopped onion and chopped green cabbage and a little bit of water.
Add potatoes.
Cover and simmer with a lid on until potatoes are tender.
Serve with red beans and cornbread.

title: easy chocolate ice cream cake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed for 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool slightly.
Turn out onto aluminum foil-covered baking sheet. Cool thoroughly and set aside.
In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, 2/3 cup syrup and chopped almonds.
Fold in whipped cream.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with aluminum foil, extending foil above side of pan.
Pour chocolate mixture into pan.
Cover and freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Lift out of pan with foil, turn out evenly on top of cake.
Trim ice cream to fit cake.
Quickly frost top and sides with whipped topping.
Drizzle with syrup.
Return to freezer.

title: french bread fantastic
directions: Mix margarine and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread on bread and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: sugar-free pistachio salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding over the Cool Whip.
Stir in pineapple and juice.
Add pecans.
Stir well.

title: easy yeast rolls(muffins; bake in muffin pan)
directions: Beat egg, mix
in sugar and melted (not hot) margarine. Add flour.
Stir
the yeast and water.	Pour into other ingredients and mix with
a
spoon.
Butter muffin pan with quite a bit of butter and	fill
full with dough.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes	or as brown as you like.
Store remaining dough in covered
bowl
in
refrigerator.
This will stay good for about a week in the refrigerator.
Will make 24 rolls.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put in container that has a tight lid.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until the top and edges are golden brown. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt, pepper and butter, then sprinkle with onion rings (as much as you like).
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven, uncovered.
Serve over rice.
Very good with green beans as a side.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put in potatoes (raw).
Mix soup, sour cream and chopped onions (optional) together; pour over potatoes.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Add crushed crackers on top of cheese and top it all off by pouring the melted margarine over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven stew
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Stir everything, mixing well, into a large iron pot.
(I use a cast iron Dutch oven.)
Cover and put on middle rack in oven at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a microsafe dish, melt butter and mix with oil.
Place chicken breasts in dish, coating breasts on both sides.
Microwave on High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 1 minute.
Turn breasts over. Microwave again at High power for 3 minutes until chicken breasts are done, not overcooked.
Set aside.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place in covered roasting pan in order listed (or cover pan with aluminum foil).
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°, then 2 hours or longer at 325°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables (especially tasty with broccoli and cauliflower).

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Stir well until mixed.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain. Combine with cheese, celery, onion, mayonnaise and pepper.
Turn mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crackers and oleo.
Sprinkle crackers over vegetable mixture.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter; mix in pecans and coconut.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 325° until slightly brown.
Stir occasionally. Let cool.
Mix milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip (add the Cool Whip a little at a time).
Equally divide the mixture into the pie shells.
Equally put coconut/pecan mixture on top.
Put as much or as little caramel on top of each pie as desired.
Freeze.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon drippings just until slightly tender.
Add other ingredients and cover with water. Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: delicious french dressing
directions: Mix in a quart jar or blender.
Shake well before using. Good on all vegetable salads.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and cube sweet potatoes.
Combine first five ingredients.
Stir in mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: banana bread(from grandma knaptly)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add egg while very hot.
Blend in other ingredients.
This type of potato salad is good with turnip greens.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking pan in 400 degree oven. Stir together ketchup & garlic; brush over wings, then roll wings in bread crumbs to coat evenly. Place in pan, turning to coat lightly with butter and bake for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving juice in 2-cup measure; add water to make 3/4 cup liquid. Stir in brown sugar, ginger, Worcestershire sauce & Tabasco. After wings have cooked 30 minutes, turn and pour on sauce; bake about 20 to 30 minutes longer or until chicken is tender, adding pineapple for last 5 minutes. Care should be taken to ensure wings are lightly browned. Makes about 4 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash berries, add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Pour over berries.
Cook for about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Don't burn.

title: quick and easy spaghetti
directions: In a deep skillet, brown the first 4 ingredients in shortening.
Add salt; stir in water.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti; cook until spaghetti is tender (about 15 minutes).
Add tomatoes and catsup; simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: cinnamon-pecan rolls
directions: Brush butter over top of each roll.
Combine cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon over each roll.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake in a greased, shallow pan in a hot oven (400°) for 12 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: schnitzel
directions: Trim tenderloin, removing any visible fat.
Cut in 4 pieces. Pound each piece to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip into eggs, coat in flour and shake off excess.

title: edith's bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to boiling point; pour over bread and beat well. Add flavoring, egg yolks, sugar and margarine.
Beat well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
When done, top with meringue and brown in hot oven.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, mix pudding mix with milk. Cook until thick. Add oil and then cake mix.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle nuts and chips over mixture.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Easy and delicious!

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Place 2 c. water in large bowl, sprinkle yeast on top.
Let dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 450 degrees for 20 minutes.
Batter keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: sister mabel's caramel corn
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil rapidly for about 5 minutes, until mixture reaches 260° on candy thermometer.
This is the hard ball stage.
You can also test this by dropping a few drops of syrup into ice water.
The syrup should form a firm ball that holds its shape, but is still pliable.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda quickly, but thoroughly.

title: pretzel delight
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 minutes

title: mazetti
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and simmer 40 - 60 minutes.
Top with cheese just before serving.

title: hamburger, sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck and drain.
Mix in other ingredients except cheese.
Put in greased 11 x 14-inch pan (glass).
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add grated cheese to top of casserole the last 15 minutes of baking time.
Be sure to cover with foil.

title: banana nog
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender; blend until smooth. Makes one serving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes coarsely; sprinkle Fruit-Fresh over grated potatoes to maintain color.
Mix salt, pepper and egg with potatoes.
Add flour; mix again.
Heat oil.
Form pancakes by squeezing excess juice from potatoes, then pat mixture dry (about 1 tablespoon flat in palm of hand).
Add pancakes to hot oil; brown 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for 1 cup cracker crumbs, together.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello junk
directions: In oblong dish, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add crushed pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir and let set.
Make a topping by cooking sugar, flour, egg, 1 cup pineapple juice and margarine together in saucepan until thick. Cool and add Cool Whip.
Spread over jello layer.
Sprinkle small amount of nuts on top for garnish.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine and cook for 12 hours in a low set oven or crock-pot.

title: green chili rice(serves 8)
directions: Cook and cool rice.
Mix sour cream with cooked rice.
Spread half of the mixture in buttered casserole.
Spread cubed cheese and chilies on rice.
Cover with remaining sour cream/rice mixture. Bake at 250° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Heat butter, brown sugar, garlic salt and soy sauce in sauce pan until melted.
Wrap 10 beans in 1/2 slice bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place in casserole and pour mixture over beans. Let refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Add remaining ingredients except coconut.
Form into balls.
Chill until firm.
Balls may be rolled in the flaked coconut immediately after shaping, if desired.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: grill fish
directions: Mix vinegar, lemon juice and soy sauce together.
Salt large fish; cut down back on both sides.
Put on grill.
Baste fish as you grill inside and out until done.
Large fish takes about 1 hour to cook.

title: tomato  soup dressing
directions: In a jar, combine all ingredients. Cover and shake. Makes 4 cups.

title: mock chili rellenos
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In large bowl, mix in first 7 ingredients.
Stir in sifted ingredients.
Pour in a pan sprayed with Pam.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.
When gets done, turn bread upside-down on plate and cut up a stick of butter or margarine on top.

title: fresh fruit dessert
directions: Crush pretzels into nut size pieces.
Melt butter in saucepan and mix in sugar, mix thoroughly.
Stir in pretzels.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: creamy pasta primavera
directions: Cook vegetables separately in boiling, salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Cook fettuccini according to package directions and drain.
Bring Ricotta cheese, milk and seasonings to a boil.
Stir in Mozzarella.
Stir in vegetables and heat. Remove from heat and add fettucini.
Toss to coat.
Serves 4.

title: confetti rice
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Add rice, carrots, celery and peas. Cook until heated through about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in bacon. Can serve with soy sauce.
Yields 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Make sure the pineapple is well blotted. Mix all ingredients together, except the pecans, in a bowl using a spoon or spatula. Set in the refrigerator until hardened. Roll in crushed pecans.

title: fruit bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, brown sugar and baking soda.
Then stir in melted margarine or butter until well combined.
Set 2 cups of the oat mixture aside for topper.
Pat the remaining oat mixture into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt, garlic salt, pizza sauce, tomato sauce and oregano.
Cook the noodles and drain.
Add cheese soup to noodles and pepperonis.
Layer meat and noodles.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes covered.
Top with mozzarella cheese for the last 15 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half lengthwise; place in dish close to each other.
Next, layer the bananas, sliced, followed by the pudding, mixed according to package directions.
Drain the pineapple; layer on top of pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat balls
directions: Form the first 7 ingredients into balls.
Put in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients.
Heat until steaming hot.
Pour over meat balls and top with biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and Pace. Mix in another bowl the soup, sour cream and olives.
Then layer corn tortillas, meat mixture, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat three times.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into dish that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grit cheese bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain.
Crumble into small bites and set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with shortening or butter.
Bring water to a boil.
Slowly add grits and salt, stirring as you add.
Simmer 4 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove grits from heat; add 2/3 of bacon. Keep remaining 1/3 to garnish.
Add eggs, 1 1/2 cups of cheese and onion flakes; mix well.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife can be inserted and comes out clean.
Top with remaining cheese and bacon; drop butter over mixture, allowing butter to melt into mixture.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Excellent for brunch.
Sausage may be substituted. Makes 12 generous servings.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Mix everything together but the potatoes, then pour over the potatoes.
Top with 2 cups corn flakes or Chex, crushed and 1/4 to 1/2 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 4-quart casserole.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix the butter, sugar and the cup of flour to a crumbly consistency and pack into an ungreased 8 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then take out of oven and cover with the following mixture.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over crust and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: big mama's lime congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water until dissolved; add cold water and stir. Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise and pineapple. Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, varying amounts of each ingredient according to your liking.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, egg, shortening and vanilla; stir in milk.
Sift and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in blueberries. Spread in 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tuna jubilee
directions: Cook spinach noodles as directed.
Melt butter in a dish.
Add drained noodles and toss.
Add cheeses and tuna and toss together lightly over low heat until warmed.
Garnish with sliced olives.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Next add flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan for 40 to 45 at 350°.

title: williamsburg breakfast
directions: In saucepan, brown sausage and onions; drain.
Put 4 cups Rice Krispies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add alternate layers of sausage, rice and cheese.
Poke holes through mixture with a knife.
Pour mixture of eggs, soup and milk over layers. Top with remaining Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: sweet potatoes pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.
